  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <!-- KEY MESSAGES BY DISCIPLINE (v2.4)            -->
  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-keymsg">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#ffe4e6;">&#127919;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Key Messages by Discipline</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Pain point &rarr; hero message &rarr; proof &rarr; objection handler &rarr; CTA. Tailor your opener to the specialty in front of you.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #e11d48; background:#fff1f2; margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card-title" style="color:#9f1239;">&#9888; PLACEHOLDER FRAMEWORK &mdash; TEAM TO REFINE</div>
      <div class="card-body" style="color:#9f1239;">Draft messaging below is a starting point based on the MiniBox+ value proposition. Marketing + Clinical should review and lock each discipline's version before national rollout.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PULMONOLOGY -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-blue">&#129729;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Pulmonology</div><div class="section-sub">Your primary call point &mdash; they own the PFT lab</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue-brand);">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Legacy body-box is expensive, room-sized, and booked out weeks. Tech-dependent, hard to staff, patients reschedule.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue-brand);">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Full PFTs &mdash; spirometry, lung volumes, DLCO &mdash; in the exam room, in under 15 minutes, without a sealed booth."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">CHEST 2021 Berger et al. validation study &mdash; MiniBox+ TLC vs. plethysmography in 100+ subjects. Same-day workup enables faster Rx decisions.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"We already have a body box."</em> &rarr; "Perfect. MiniBox+ is for satellite offices and overflow days &mdash; you keep the box for complex cases and recover weeks of scheduling capacity."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#eff6ff;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Schedule a 30-minute in-office demo. Bring a Berger reprint and your ROI calculator.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- ALLERGY / IMMUNOLOGY -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-teal">&#127793;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Allergy / Immunology</div><div class="section-sub">Asthma workup volume &mdash; MiniBox+ adds lung volumes without a booth</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Running spirometry only &mdash; referring out for lung volumes / DLCO loses patients and revenue.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Keep your asthma patients in-house with full PFTs &mdash; not just spirometry. One device. One visit. Full 94010 + 94726 + 94729 billing."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Asthma/COPD overlap patients need lung volumes to distinguish obstructive from restrictive. Air trapping detection changes Rx.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"We just send them for a formal PFT."</em> &rarr; "How many actually go? MiniBox+ captures the 40%+ who no-show the referral &mdash; that's both clinical follow-through and billable revenue."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#ecfdf5;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Demo + ROI calc showing incremental 94726/94729 revenue at their current spirometry volume.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- PRIMARY CARE -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#127973;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Primary Care / Family Medicine</div><div class="section-sub">Underpenetrated segment &mdash; lead with CPT revenue, not clinical depth</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--amber);">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Chronic cough, dyspnea, smoking history &mdash; all referred out. Loses patients, loses revenue, delays diagnosis.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--amber);">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Add a revenue line. Diagnose COPD and asthma at the point of care. ~$150 per full PFT, 10&ndash;15 minutes, staff-friendly."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">3 PFTs/week &times; 48 weeks = ~$21,700/year incremental revenue. Device pays for itself in under 18 months.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"We're not a PFT lab."</em> &rarr; "You don't need to be. MiniBox+ was built for exam-room use. Your MA runs it. Results in the EMR in minutes."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#fef3e2;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Lead with the ROI calculator (Daily Hub tab). Demo is secondary &mdash; revenue story closes them.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- CARDIOLOGY -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#fee2e2;">&#10084;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Cardiology</div><div class="section-sub">Dyspnea workup &mdash; rule out pulmonary before sending to stress</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #dc2626;">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Dyspnea is cardiac vs. pulmonary until proven otherwise. Sending every patient out for PFTs delays workup.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #dc2626;">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Rule out pulmonary at the same visit. Full PFTs before the stress test, not three weeks later."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">CHF with restrictive pattern, obesity hypoventilation, and COPD overlap are all identified faster with in-office PFTs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"That's what the pulmonologist is for."</em> &rarr; "Agreed &mdash; for complex cases. MiniBox+ is your first-pass screen to decide who needs a pulm referral and who doesn't."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#fef2f2;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Target practices running in-office stress testing &mdash; they already value same-visit diagnostics.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- PEDIATRICS -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#dbeafe;">&#129489;&#8205;&#9877;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Pediatrics</div><div class="section-sub">School-age asthma &mdash; kids can perform the test, booths intimidate</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Pediatric asthma management runs on symptom diaries. Objective lung function data is rare &mdash; booths scare kids.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Open-format PFTs your patients aren't afraid of. Objective asthma control data, without sealing a 7-year-old in a box."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">MiniBox+ pediatric usability data &mdash; non-booth design, shorter test time, higher first-attempt success.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"Insurance coverage for kids?"</em> &rarr; "94010/94726/94729 codes are age-agnostic. School-age kids clear cleanly on commercial and Medicaid."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#eff6ff;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Target large multi-provider pediatric practices with asthma programs. Clinical champion = the asthma lead.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- OCCUPATIONAL MEDICINE -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#fef3c7;">&#128736;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Occupational Medicine</div><div class="section-sub">OSHA respiratory surveillance &mdash; high-volume, protocol-driven</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #d97706;">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">OSHA 29 CFR 1910.134 respiratory clearance &mdash; hundreds of spirometries, but missing the lung volume component for full workup.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #d97706;">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Upgrade your surveillance from spirometry to full PFT &mdash; same test time, same throughput, catches restrictive disease OSHA spirometry misses."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Silica, asbestos, and dust exposures are restrictive patterns. Spirometry alone under-detects. Lung volumes + DLCO = complete.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"Employers won't pay for more."</em> &rarr; "You don't bill the employer &mdash; you bill the symptomatic patient's insurance when the surveillance spirometry is abnormal. New revenue line, not employer cost."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#fffbeb;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Target large occ-med clinics with OSHA surveillance contracts. Demo throughput &mdash; they care about tests/day.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- v2.5: US Roster is merged into People & Contacts. Policies & Procedures is merged into Ops & Admin. -->

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- v2.19: RHEUMATOLOGY PFT ESTIMATOR     -->
  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-rheum">
    <style>
      #tab-rheum, #tab-rheum .rhp { --rht:#0d8aa6; --rht-deep:#0a6075; --rht-wash:#eaf5f8; --rht-line:#cfe6ec; --rhg:#c98a2b; --rhink:#0e2a3a; --rhsoft:#3a5567; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-lede { font-size:14.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); max-width:680px; line-height:1.6; margin:2px 0 4px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-sec { margin-top:26px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-sec-head { display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:11px; margin-bottom:14px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-sec-num { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono','Consolas',monospace; font-size:13px; font-weight:600; color:var(--rhg); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-sec-title { font-size:18px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:-.01em; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-steps { display:grid; gap:10px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-step { display:grid; grid-template-columns:auto 1fr; gap:16px; align-items:start; background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:12px; padding:15px 18px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-step .rhp-n { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:24px; font-weight:600; color:var(--rht); line-height:1; min-width:26px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-step h4 { font-size:14.5px; font-weight:700; color:var(--rhink); margin:0 0 3px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-step p { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin:0; line-height:1.55; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-stats { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:12px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-stat { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-left:4px solid var(--rht); border-radius:11px; padding:16px 18px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-stat .rhp-big { font-size:30px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); line-height:1; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-stat .rhp-lbl { margin-top:7px; font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.45; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-grid2 { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:14px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-ref { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:12px; padding:18px 20px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-ref h4 { font-size:11.5px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.11em; color:var(--rht-deep); font-weight:800; margin:0 0 12px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-cpt { display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:baseline; padding:8px 0; border-bottom:1px dashed var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-cpt:last-child { border-bottom:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-cpt-code { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-weight:600; font-size:16px; color:var(--rht); min-width:58px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-cpt-desc { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhsoft); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-note { margin-top:12px; font-size:12px; color:var(--rhsoft); background:var(--rht-wash); padding:10px 12px; border-radius:8px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-note b { color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum table.rhp-mini { width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:12.5px; }
      #tab-rheum table.rhp-mini th { text-align:left; font-size:10px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.08em; color:var(--rhsoft); font-weight:700; padding:0 8px 8px 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum table.rhp-mini td { padding:8px 8px 8px 0; border-bottom:1px dashed var(--rht-line); color:var(--rhsoft); vertical-align:top; }
      #tab-rheum table.rhp-mini tr:last-child td { border-bottom:none; }
      #tab-rheum table.rhp-mini td:first-child { color:var(--rhink); font-weight:600; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-obj, #tab-rheum .rhp-fin { padding:11px 0; border-bottom:1px dashed var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-obj:last-child, #tab-rheum .rhp-fin:last-child { border-bottom:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-obj .rhp-q { font-weight:700; font-size:13px; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-obj .rhp-a { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:3px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-fin .rhp-t { font-weight:700; font-size:13px; color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-fin .rhp-d { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:2px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qs { display:grid; gap:9px; counter-reset:rhpq; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qitem { display:grid; grid-template-columns:auto 1fr; gap:13px; align-items:start; padding:13px 16px; background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:11px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qitem::before { counter-increment:rhpq; content:counter(rhpq); font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-weight:600; font-size:16px; color:#fff; background:var(--rht); width:28px; height:28px; border-radius:50%; display:grid; place-items:center; line-height:1; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qitem p { font-size:13.5px; color:var(--rhink); margin:0; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qitem.rhp-closer { border-color:var(--rhg); background:linear-gradient(180deg,#fff,#fdf6ea); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qitem.rhp-closer::before { background:var(--rhg); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-qtag { display:inline-block; font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); margin-bottom:3px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhsub-nav { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:8px; margin:4px 0 18px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhsub-btn { font-size:13px; font-weight:700; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); color:var(--gray-600); background:#fff; border-radius:999px; padding:8px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; }
      #tab-rheum .rhsub-btn:hover { border-color:#0d8aa6; color:#0a6075; }
      #tab-rheum .rhsub-btn.on { border-color:#0d8aa6; background:#eaf5f8; color:#0a6075; }
      /* PFT Suite used to leave the toolkit. It now loads in-place like every other
         view, so it gets the plain pill — no arrow, no "new tab" signal. */

      /* ---- PFT Suite, embedded ---- */
      #tab-rheum .rhps-wrap { border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; background:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-bar { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; padding:13px 18px; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#f3fafc,#eaf5f8); border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-t { font-size:15px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-off { font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.11em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rht-deep); background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:999px; padding:3px 9px; margin-left:7px; vertical-align:middle; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-s { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:3px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-btns { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-b { font-size:13px; font-weight:700; border:none; border-radius:999px; padding:9px 17px; cursor:pointer; background:var(--rht); color:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-b:hover { filter:brightness(1.06); }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-b.ghost { background:#fff; color:var(--rht-deep); border:1.5px solid var(--rht); }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-frame { position:relative; background:#fafaf8; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-frame iframe { display:block; width:100%; height:calc(100vh - 300px); min-height:620px; border:0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhps-load { position:absolute; inset:0; display:grid; place-items:center; font-size:13px; font-weight:700; color:var(--rhsoft); pointer-events:none; }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #tab-rheum .rhps-bar { flex-direction:column; align-items:stretch; } #tab-rheum .rhps-btns button { flex:1 1 auto; } #tab-rheum .rhps-frame iframe { height:calc(100vh - 240px); min-height:520px; } }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:14px; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#f3fafc,#eaf5f8); border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); border-left:5px solid var(--rht); border-radius:12px; padding:15px 18px; margin:0 0 16px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-h { font-size:15px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-s { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:3px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-btns { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-btns button { font-size:13px; font-weight:700; border:none; border-radius:999px; padding:10px 18px; cursor:pointer; background:var(--rht); color:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-btns button:hover { filter:brightness(1.06); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-btns button.ghost { background:#fff; color:var(--rht-deep); border:1.5px solid var(--rht); }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #tab-rheum .rhp-grid2, #tab-rheum .rhp-stats { grid-template-columns:1fr; } #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta { flex-direction:column; align-items:stretch; } #tab-rheum .rhp-files-cta-btns button { flex:1 1 auto; } }

      /* ---- v2.20: Interpretation Composer ---- */
      #tab-rheum .rhc { display:grid; gap:16px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-card { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-head { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; padding:16px 20px; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#0a6075,#084c5d); color:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-head h3 { margin:0; font-size:17px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-.01em; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-head p { margin:3px 0 0; font-size:12px; color:#9fd0dd; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-timer { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono','Consolas',monospace; font-size:22px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.04em; background:rgba(255,255,255,.12); border-radius:10px; padding:7px 14px; min-width:104px; text-align:center; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-timer.run { background:rgba(107,209,140,.22); color:#c7f3d6; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-timer-lbl { display:block; font-family:inherit; font-size:9px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9fd0dd; margin-top:2px; font-weight:700; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-body { padding:18px 20px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-steps { display:grid; gap:16px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-step-h { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:10px; margin-bottom:9px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-step-n { width:24px; height:24px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--rht); color:#fff; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; font-weight:600; display:grid; place-items:center; flex-shrink:0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-step-t { font-size:14.5px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-step-s { font-size:12px; color:var(--rhsoft); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-vals { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(172px,1fr)); gap:10px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val { background:#fafaf8; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:10px; padding:10px 12px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val label { display:block; font-size:11px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:.01em; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val .rhc-hint { display:block; font-size:10px; color:#999; margin:1px 0 6px; line-height:1.35; }
      /* Two columns, four children (input,tag,input,tag) → the z row and the % row stack.
         Each input then gets the full card width, so "-3.78" can never be clipped. */
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val-row { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr auto; gap:6px; align-items:center; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val input { width:100%; min-width:0; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono','Consolas',monospace; font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:var(--rht-deep); border:1px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:7px; padding:6px 9px; background:#fff; text-align:right; letter-spacing:.01em; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val input::placeholder { font-size:12px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:.02em; color:#b9b9b4; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val input:focus { outline:none; border-color:#0d8aa6; box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(13,138,166,.13); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val input::-webkit-outer-spin-button, #tab-rheum .rhc-val input::-webkit-inner-spin-button { -webkit-appearance:none; margin:0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val input[type=number] { -moz-appearance:textfield; appearance:textfield; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val-tag { font-size:9.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9a9a94; align-self:center; min-width:26px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-val-warn { display:none; font-size:10.5px; font-weight:600; color:#b45309; background:#fffbeb; border:1px solid #fde68a; border-radius:6px; padding:5px 8px; margin-top:5px; line-height:1.45; }
      /* Signature block — typed name/date beat fighting an underscore line inside a textarea. */
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr)); gap:10px; margin-bottom:11px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign-f { background:#f4fbfc; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:10px; padding:10px 12px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign-f label { display:block; font-size:11px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign-f .rhc-hint { display:block; font-size:10px; color:#999; margin:1px 0 6px; line-height:1.35; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign-f input { width:100%; min-width:0; font-family:inherit; font-size:13.5px; font-weight:600; color:var(--rht-deep); border:1px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:7px; padding:7px 9px; background:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign-f input:focus { outline:none; border-color:#0d8aa6; box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(13,138,166,.13); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-sign-f input::placeholder { font-weight:500; color:#b9b9b4; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-where { display:flex; gap:9px; align-items:flex-start; background:#f4fbfc; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-left:3px solid var(--rht); border-radius:8px; padding:10px 12px; margin-top:11px; font-size:11.5px; line-height:1.5; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-where b { color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-btnrow { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:8px; margin-top:12px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-btn { font-size:12.5px; font-weight:700; border-radius:999px; padding:9px 17px; cursor:pointer; border:1.5px solid var(--rht); background:var(--rht); color:#fff; transition:all .12s; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-btn:hover { filter:brightness(1.07); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-btn.ghost { background:#fff; color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-btn.ghost:hover { background:#eaf5f8; filter:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gates { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(190px,1fr)); gap:10px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gate { border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:11px; padding:12px 14px; background:#fff; opacity:.5; transition:all .18s; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gate.live { opacity:1; border-color:#0d8aa6; background:#f3fafc; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gate-n { font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rht); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gate-q { font-size:13px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); margin-top:3px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gate-a { font-size:12px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:5px; line-height:1.45; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-gate-a b { color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict { border-radius:12px; padding:15px 18px; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); background:linear-gradient(180deg,#f3fafc,#eaf5f8); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict.hit { border-color:#c98b1d; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#fffaf0,#fdf1dc); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict-lbl { font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.13em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhsoft); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict-v { font-size:20px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rht-deep); margin-top:3px; letter-spacing:-.015em; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict.hit .rhc-verdict-v { color:#9a6510; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict-sev { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:5px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-verdict-sev select { font-size:12.5px; font-weight:700; border:1px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:6px; padding:3px 7px; margin-left:5px; background:#fff; color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-out { width:100%; min-height:190px; font-family:'Georgia',serif; font-size:14px; line-height:1.65; color:var(--rhink); border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:11px; padding:15px 17px; background:#fffef9; resize:vertical; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-out:focus { outline:none; border-color:#0d8aa6; box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(13,138,166,.11); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-flag { display:flex; gap:11px; align-items:flex-start; border-radius:11px; padding:13px 16px; margin-top:12px; border:1px solid #e6c98a; border-left:4px solid #c98b1d; background:#fffaf0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-flag-i { font-size:17px; line-height:1; flex-shrink:0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-flag-t { font-size:13px; font-weight:800; color:#9a6510; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-flag-d { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:3px; line-height:1.55; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-note { font-size:11.5px; color:#8a8a8a; line-height:1.55; margin-top:11px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo { display:none; margin-top:12px; border:1.5px dashed var(--rht); background:#f2fafc; border-radius:12px; padding:13px 15px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo.on { display:block; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo-h { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo-tag { font-size:10.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#fff; background:var(--rht); border-radius:999px; padding:3px 10px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo-t { font-size:13px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo-d { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.6; margin-top:7px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-demo-d b { color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-toast { position:fixed; left:50%; bottom:28px; transform:translate(-50%,14px); background:#0a6075; color:#fff; font-size:13px; font-weight:700; padding:11px 22px; border-radius:999px; opacity:0; pointer-events:none; transition:all .22s; z-index:9999; }
      #tab-rheum .rhc-toast.on { opacity:1; transform:translate(-50%,0); }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #tab-rheum .rhc-head { flex-direction:column; align-items:stretch; text-align:center; } }

      /* ---- the chain: three questions, three tools ---- */
      #tab-rheum .rhx { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:14px; overflow:hidden; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-h { padding:15px 20px 0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-h h4 { margin:0; font-size:15.5px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-h p { margin:4px 0 0; font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.55; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:0; padding:15px 20px 18px; position:relative; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-step { padding:0 16px; border-left:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-step:first-child { border-left:0; padding-left:0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-who { font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.13em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-q { font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); margin-top:4px; line-height:1.35; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-tool { font-size:11.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:5px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-go { margin-top:10px; font-size:12px; font-weight:800; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-deep); background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; border-radius:999px; padding:8px 15px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; animation:rhxGlow 2.2s ease-in-out infinite; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-go:hover { background:var(--rht-deep); transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(13,138,166,.45); animation:none; }
      @keyframes rhxGlow { 0%,100% { box-shadow:0 0 0 0 rgba(13,138,166,.45); } 50% { box-shadow:0 0 12px 3px rgba(13,138,166,.4); } }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-go.here { animation:none; background:#fff; color:var(--rht-deep); border:1.5px dashed var(--rht); opacity:.75; cursor:default; box-shadow:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-go.here:hover { background:#fff; color:var(--rht-deep); transform:none; box-shadow:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhx-foot { font-size:11.5px; color:#8a8a8a; line-height:1.6; padding:0 20px 16px; }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #tab-rheum .rhx-grid { grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:16px; } #tab-rheum .rhx-step { border-left:0; padding:0; border-top:1px solid var(--rht-line); padding-top:14px; } #tab-rheum .rhx-step:first-child { border-top:0; padding-top:0; } }

      /* ---- Rehearse the Room: the three-person act ---- */
      #tab-rheum .rhact-cta { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; background:linear-gradient(120deg,#0e2a3a,#0a6075); border-radius:14px; padding:16px 20px; margin:12px 0 2px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhact-cta-mask { font-size:30px; line-height:1; flex:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhact-cta-h { font-size:15px; font-weight:800; color:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhact-cta-s { font-size:12.5px; color:#bcd9e2; margin-top:2px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhact-cta-btn { margin-left:auto; flex:none; font-size:13px; font-weight:800; color:#0a6075; background:#fff; border:0; border-radius:999px; padding:10px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; animation:rhactGlowW 2.2s ease-in-out infinite; }
      #tab-rheum .rhact-cta-btn:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(255,255,255,.4); animation:none; }
      @keyframes rhactGlowW { 0%,100% { box-shadow:0 0 0 0 rgba(255,255,255,.35); } 50% { box-shadow:0 0 14px 3px rgba(255,255,255,.3); } }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #tab-rheum .rhact-cta { flex-wrap:wrap; } #tab-rheum .rhact-cta-btn { margin-left:0; } }

      /* ---- "See the report" — where every number actually comes from ---- */
      #rhrep-overlay { display:none; position:fixed; inset:0; z-index:99991; background:rgba(14,42,58,.66); align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:18px; }
      #rhrep-overlay.on { display:flex; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-card { background:#fff; border-radius:18px; max-width:860px; width:100%; max-height:92vh; overflow:auto; box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35); animation:rhactUp .22s ease; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-top { position:sticky; top:0; background:#fff; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); padding:16px 24px 13px; display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:14px; z-index:2; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-tag { font-size:10px; letter-spacing:.16em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-title { font-size:19px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:-.01em; margin-top:4px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-sub { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:4px; line-height:1.5; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-x { border:0; background:none; font-size:16px; color:#8a8a8a; cursor:pointer; padding:4px 8px; flex:none; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-x:hover { color:var(--rhink); }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-body { padding:18px 24px 24px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-sheet { border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:12px; overflow:hidden; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-head { background:var(--rht-deep); color:#fff; padding:11px 16px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:6px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-brand { font-weight:800; font-size:14px; letter-spacing:-.01em; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-kind { font-size:11px; opacity:.85; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-demo-note { background:#fff8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #f0dfb8; color:#8a6520; font-size:11.5px; font-weight:700; padding:7px 16px; text-align:center; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-pt { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(112px,1fr)); gap:10px 14px; padding:13px 16px; background:var(--rht-wash); border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-pt div span { display:block; font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.11em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rhsoft); font-weight:800; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-pt div b { font-size:13.5px; color:var(--rhink); }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-sec { font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.11em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhsoft); padding:13px 16px 5px; }
      #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t { width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px; }
      #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t th { text-align:right; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:.07em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rhsoft); font-weight:800; padding:5px 10px; border-bottom:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t th:first-child, #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t td:first-child { text-align:left; }
      #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t td { text-align:right; padding:7px 10px; border-bottom:1px solid #eef4f6; color:var(--rhink); font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums; }
      #rhrep-overlay tr.rhrep-use { background:#f3fbfd; cursor:pointer; }
      #rhrep-overlay tr.rhrep-use:hover { background:#e2f4f9; }
      #rhrep-overlay tr.rhrep-use td { border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #rhrep-overlay tr.rhrep-use td:first-child { box-shadow:inset 3px 0 0 var(--rht); font-weight:700; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-pin { display:inline-grid; place-items:center; width:17px; height:17px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--rht); color:#fff; font-size:10px; font-weight:800; margin-right:7px; vertical-align:1px; }
      #rhrep-overlay td.rhrep-z { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-weight:700; }
      #rhrep-overlay td.rhrep-z.low { color:#b4432c; }
      #rhrep-overlay td.rhrep-z.ok { color:#1c7a4a; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-flag { font-size:10.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.04em; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-flag.low { color:#b4432c; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-flag.ok { color:#1c7a4a; }
      #rhrep-overlay tr.rhrep-sec2 td { color:var(--rhsoft); font-size:12px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-clicknote { font-size:12px; color:var(--rht-deep); background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:9px; padding:9px 13px; margin:14px 0 0; font-weight:700; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-z-explain { margin-top:16px; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:12px; padding:15px 17px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-z-explain h4 { font-size:14.5px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); margin-bottom:7px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-z-explain p { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.62; margin-bottom:9px; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-scale { position:relative; height:38px; margin:13px 0 7px; }
      /* z scale runs -5 .. +3, so x% = ((z+5)/8)*100. LLN (z -1.645) lands at 41.9%. */
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-scale-bar { position:absolute; left:0; right:0; top:13px; height:6px; border-radius:3px; background:linear-gradient(90deg,#e8b4a5 0%,#f2d9a8 36%,#cfe8d8 44%,#cfe8d8 100%); }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-scale-lln { position:absolute; top:5px; bottom:9px; width:2px; background:#c98a2b; left:41.9%; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-scale-lbl { position:absolute; top:24px; font-size:10px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhsoft); transform:translateX(-50%); white-space:nowrap; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-dot { position:absolute; top:11px; width:10px; height:10px; border-radius:50%; background:#b4432c; border:2px solid #fff; box-shadow:0 0 0 1px #b4432c; transform:translateX(-50%); }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-dot.ok { background:#1c7a4a; box-shadow:0 0 0 1px #1c7a4a; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-dot b { position:absolute; top:-17px; left:50%; transform:translateX(-50%); font-size:9.5px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhsoft); white-space:nowrap; }
      #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-foot { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:9px; margin-top:16px; }
      @media (max-width:640px){
        #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-body { padding:14px 13px 18px; }
        #rhrep-overlay .rhrep-top { padding:14px 15px 11px; }
        #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t { font-size:12px; }
        #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t td, #rhrep-overlay table.rhrep-t th { padding:6px 6px; }
      }

      #rhact-overlay { display:none; position:fixed; inset:0; z-index:99990; background:rgba(14,42,58,.66); align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:18px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-card { background:#fff; border-radius:18px; max-width:660px; width:100%; max-height:92vh; overflow:auto; box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35); animation:rhactUp .22s ease; padding:20px 26px 22px; }
      @keyframes rhactUp { from { transform:translateY(14px); opacity:0; } to { transform:none; opacity:1; } }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-top { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:14px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-steps { display:flex; gap:7px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-dot { width:8px; height:8px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--rht-line); transition:all .15s; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-dot.on { background:var(--rht); transform:scale(1.35); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-x { border:0; background:none; font-size:16px; color:#8a8a8a; cursor:pointer; padding:4px 8px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-x:hover { color:var(--rhink); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-tag { font-size:10px; letter-spacing:.16em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-title { font-size:21px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:-.01em; margin:6px 0 10px; line-height:1.3; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-cast1 { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:11px; margin-bottom:12px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-av { font-size:30px; line-height:1; background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:50%; width:52px; height:52px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; flex:none; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-who { font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-bubble { position:relative; background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:14px; padding:14px 18px; font-size:19px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); line-height:1.35; margin:0 0 16px 24px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-bubble:before { content:''; position:absolute; top:-9px; left:26px; width:16px; height:16px; background:var(--rht-wash); border-left:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-top:1px solid var(--rht-line); transform:rotate(45deg); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-lbl { font-size:10px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; margin-top:13px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-lbl.gold { color:var(--rhg); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-lbl.teal { color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-p { font-size:13.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.6; margin:4px 0 0; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-cast { display:flex; gap:10px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:16px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-chip { font-size:13px; font-weight:700; color:var(--rht-deep); background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:999px; padding:8px 15px; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-open { display:inline-block; margin-top:16px; font-size:12.5px; font-weight:800; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-deep); background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; border-radius:999px; padding:9px 17px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; animation:rhxGlow 2.2s ease-in-out infinite; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-open:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(13,138,166,.45); animation:none; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-foot { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; margin-top:20px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-nav { font-size:12.5px; font-weight:700; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); background:#fff; color:var(--rhsoft); border-radius:999px; padding:8px 16px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-nav:hover { border-color:var(--rht); color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-nav.next, #rhact-overlay .rhact-nav.done { border-color:var(--rht-deep); background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; font-weight:800; }
      #rhact-overlay .rhact-nav.next:hover, #rhact-overlay .rhact-nav.done:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(13,138,166,.45); }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #rhact-overlay .rhact-card { padding:16px 18px 18px; } #rhact-overlay .rhact-bubble { font-size:16.5px; margin-left:12px; } #rhact-overlay .rhact-title { font-size:18px; } }

      /* ---------- The Whetstone: recall drills off the playbook itself ----------
         Any card carrying .rhp-drill is clickable and opens the matching deck,
         so the thing you just read is the thing you get quizzed on. ---------- */
      #tab-rheum .rhp-drill { cursor:pointer; transition:all .14s; border-radius:14px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-drill:hover { border-color:var(--rht); box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(13,138,166,.16); transform:translateY(-1px); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-drill:focus-visible { outline:2px solid var(--rht); outline-offset:2px; }
      /* The grid cards (.rhp-steps/.rhp-stats/.rhp-qs) carry no padding of their
         own — give them a little so the hover wash has something to fill. */
      #tab-rheum .rhp-steps.rhp-drill, #tab-rheum .rhp-stats.rhp-drill, #tab-rheum .rhp-qs.rhp-drill { padding:12px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-steps.rhp-drill:hover, #tab-rheum .rhp-stats.rhp-drill:hover, #tab-rheum .rhp-qs.rhp-drill:hover { background:var(--rht-wash); }
      /* Badge sits IN FLOW at the top right — absolute positioning collided with
         card titles at narrow widths. On grids it spans the full row. */
      #tab-rheum .rhp-drill-tag { grid-column:1/-1; justify-self:end; width:max-content; margin:0 0 4px auto; font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.1em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rht-deep); background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:999px; padding:3px 9px; opacity:.78; transition:all .14s; pointer-events:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-drill:hover .rhp-drill-tag { opacity:1; background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; border-color:var(--rht-deep); }

      /* Entry banner — same shape as "Rehearse the room" so the two read as a pair */
      #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; background:linear-gradient(120deg,#0e2a3a,#1d6b52); border-radius:14px; padding:16px 20px; margin:10px 0 2px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta-mask { font-size:30px; line-height:1; flex:none; }
      #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta-h { font-size:15px; font-weight:800; color:#fff; }
      #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta-s { font-size:12.5px; color:#c3ded1; margin-top:2px; line-height:1.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta-btn { margin-left:auto; flex:none; font-size:13px; font-weight:800; color:#14523e; background:#fff; border:0; border-radius:999px; padding:10px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; animation:rhactGlowW 2.2s ease-in-out infinite; }
      #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta-btn:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(255,255,255,.4); animation:none; }
      @media(max-width:720px){ #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta { flex-wrap:wrap; } #tab-rheum .rhfc-cta-btn { margin-left:0; } }

      /* ---------- the flashcard overlay ---------- */
      #rhfc-overlay { display:none; position:fixed; inset:0; z-index:99992; background:rgba(14,42,58,.72); align-items:center; justify-content:center; padding:18px; }
      #rhfc-overlay.on { display:flex; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-card { background:#fff; border-radius:18px; max-width:640px; width:100%; max-height:94vh; overflow:auto; box-shadow:0 24px 70px rgba(0,0,0,.35); animation:rhactUp .22s ease; padding:18px 24px 20px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-top { display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-tag { font-size:10px; letter-spacing:.16em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-title { font-size:19px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:-.01em; margin-top:3px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-sub { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:4px; line-height:1.5; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-x { border:0; background:none; font-size:16px; color:#8a8a8a; cursor:pointer; padding:4px 8px; flex:none; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-x:hover { color:var(--rhink); }

      /* deck picker */
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-decks { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(210px,1fr)); gap:10px; margin-top:16px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-deck { text-align:left; background:#fff; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:13px; padding:13px 15px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .13s; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-deck:hover { border-color:var(--rht); background:var(--rht-wash); transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 5px 16px rgba(13,138,166,.16); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-deck-h { font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-deck-n { font-size:11.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:3px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-deck-score { display:inline-block; margin-top:7px; font-size:10.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.04em; border-radius:999px; padding:3px 9px; background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-deck-score.gold { background:#fff6e3; border-color:#f0dfb8; color:#8a6520; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-all { display:block; width:100%; margin-top:12px; font-size:13px; font-weight:800; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-deep); background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; border-radius:999px; padding:11px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; animation:rhxGlow 2.2s ease-in-out infinite; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-all:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(13,138,166,.45); animation:none; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-howto { font-size:12px; color:var(--rhsoft); background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:10px; padding:10px 13px; margin-top:14px; line-height:1.6; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-howto b { color:var(--rht-deep); }

      /* progress */
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-prog { height:5px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--rht-line); margin:14px 0 4px; overflow:hidden; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-prog i { display:block; height:100%; background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); transition:width .25s ease; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-meta { display:flex; justify-content:space-between; font-size:11px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.05em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rhsoft); }

      /* the card itself — click anywhere to flip */
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-face { position:relative; margin-top:12px; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:15px; padding:26px 24px; min-height:196px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; justify-content:center; cursor:pointer; background:linear-gradient(160deg,#fbfeff,#f2fafc); transition:all .16s; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-face:hover { border-color:var(--rht); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-face.flipped { background:linear-gradient(160deg,#fff,#fff); border-color:var(--rht); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-side { font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.16em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); margin-bottom:9px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-q { font-size:19.5px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); line-height:1.38; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-a { font-size:15px; color:var(--rhink); line-height:1.62; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-a b { color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-a .rhfc-hi { display:inline-block; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-weight:700; background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:6px; padding:1px 7px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-qsmall { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); font-weight:700; margin-bottom:10px; line-height:1.45; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-hint { font-size:12px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:12px; font-style:italic; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-flipnote { position:absolute; bottom:10px; right:14px; font-size:10.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rht-deep); opacity:.55; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-anim { animation:rhfcIn .2s ease; }
      @keyframes rhfcIn { from { transform:translateY(8px) scale(.99); opacity:0; } to { transform:none; opacity:1; } }

      /* grade row */
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-grade { display:flex; gap:10px; margin-top:13px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-g { flex:1; font-size:13.5px; font-weight:800; border-radius:999px; padding:12px 14px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); background:#fff; color:var(--rhsoft); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-g.again { border-color:#e2b7a9; color:#a8412a; background:#fdf6f3; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-g.again:hover { background:#f9e6df; transform:translateY(-1px); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-g.got { border-color:#1c7a4a; background:linear-gradient(135deg,#2a9c62,#1c7a4a); color:#fff; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-g.got:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(28,122,74,.4); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-g small { display:block; font-size:10px; font-weight:700; opacity:.72; margin-top:2px; letter-spacing:.04em; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-reveal { margin-top:13px; width:100%; font-size:13.5px; font-weight:800; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-deep); background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; border-radius:999px; padding:12px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-reveal:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(13,138,166,.45); }

      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-foot { display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:10px; margin-top:14px; padding-top:12px; border-top:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-link { font-size:12px; font-weight:700; background:none; border:0; color:var(--rhsoft); cursor:pointer; padding:4px 2px; text-decoration:underline; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-link:hover { color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-keys { font-size:10.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); letter-spacing:.03em; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-keys kbd { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:10px; background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:4px; padding:1px 5px; margin:0 1px; }

      /* results */
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-score { text-align:center; padding:20px 0 6px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-score-big { font-size:52px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rht-deep); letter-spacing:-.03em; line-height:1; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-score-lbl { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:7px; font-weight:700; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-score-note { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhink); margin-top:12px; line-height:1.6; background:var(--rht-wash); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:11px; padding:12px 15px; text-align:left; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-missed { margin-top:14px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-missed h5 { font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); margin-bottom:7px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-missed li { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhink); line-height:1.55; padding:7px 0 7px 14px; border-bottom:1px solid #eef4f6; list-style:none; position:relative; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-missed li:before { content:''; position:absolute; left:0; top:13px; width:5px; height:5px; border-radius:50%; background:#c2553a; }
      /* ---- Training view. Restrained on purpose: hairlines and type, no
         emoji, no saturated fills. The playbook is loud enough. ---- */
      #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:16px; margin:14px 0 4px; padding:13px 0; border-top:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline-txt { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.55; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline-txt b { color:var(--rhink); }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline-em { font-weight:800; color:var(--rht-deep); letter-spacing:.02em; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline-btn { margin-left:auto; flex:none; font-size:12px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rht-deep); background:none; border:1.5px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:999px; padding:9px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .13s; }
      #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline-btn:hover { border-color:var(--rht-deep); background:var(--rht-wash); }
      @media(max-width:640px){ #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline { flex-wrap:wrap; gap:10px; } #tab-rheum .rhp-trainline-btn { margin-left:0; } }

      #tab-rheum .rhtr-head { padding-bottom:16px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rht-line); margin-bottom:20px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-kicker { font-size:10px; letter-spacing:.22em; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhg); }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-h { font-size:26px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:-.02em; margin:7px 0 0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-s { font-size:14px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.65; margin:8px 0 0; max-width:640px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-pair { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(300px,1fr)); gap:16px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod { position:relative; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:14px; padding:22px 22px 20px; background:linear-gradient(170deg,#fbfdfe,#f5fafb); display:flex; flex-direction:column; transition:all .15s; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod:hover { border-color:var(--rht); box-shadow:0 8px 26px rgba(13,138,166,.13); }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-n { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:11px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.14em; color:var(--rht-deep); opacity:.5; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-h { font-size:21px; font-weight:800; color:var(--rhink); letter-spacing:-.015em; margin-top:8px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-tag { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rhsoft); margin-top:6px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-s { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.68; margin:12px 0 0; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-track { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:9px; margin-top:16px; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-track .pips { display:flex; gap:5px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-track .pips i { width:18px; height:5px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--rht-line); }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-track .pips i.on { background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-cast { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:6px; margin-top:16px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-cast span { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:10.5px; letter-spacing:.06em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rhsoft); border:1px solid var(--rht-line); border-radius:999px; padding:4px 11px; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-btn { margin-top:auto; align-self:flex-start; margin-top:20px; font-size:12.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#fff; background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); border:0; border-radius:999px; padding:12px 26px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .13s; }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-mod-btn:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 5px 18px rgba(13,138,166,.4); }
      #tab-rheum .rhtr-note { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--rhsoft); line-height:1.6; margin-top:18px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid var(--rht-line); }

      /* Track strip on the menu + the "what's next" band on the results screen.
         Both exist so the overlay always points at a next move. */
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-track { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-top:14px; padding:11px 14px; border:1px solid var(--rht-line); background:var(--rht-wash); border-radius:11px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-track-pips { display:flex; gap:6px; flex:none; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-track-pips i { width:22px; height:6px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--rht-line); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-track-pips i.on { background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-track-lbl { font-size:11.5px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.04em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-next { font-size:13px; color:var(--rhink); line-height:1.6; margin-top:16px; padding:12px 15px; border-radius:11px; border:1px solid #cfe4d9; background:linear-gradient(120deg,#f2f9f5,#eef7f9); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-next b { color:#14523e; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-exit { display:block; width:100%; margin-top:10px; font-size:12.5px; font-weight:800; border:1.5px solid #1d6b52; background:linear-gradient(120deg,#0e2a3a,#1d6b52); color:#fff; border-radius:999px; padding:11px 18px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-exit:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(29,107,82,.42); }
      @media(max-width:560px){ #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-track { flex-wrap:wrap; gap:8px; } }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-again-btns { display:flex; gap:10px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:16px; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-again-btns button { flex:1; min-width:150px; font-size:13px; font-weight:800; border-radius:999px; padding:11px 16px; cursor:pointer; transition:all .12s; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); background:#fff; color:var(--rhsoft); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-again-btns button:hover { border-color:var(--rht); color:var(--rht-deep); }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-again-btns button.primary { border-color:var(--rht-deep); background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--rht),var(--rht-deep)); color:#fff; }
      #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-again-btns button.primary:hover { transform:translateY(-1px); box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(13,138,166,.45); }
      @media(max-width:720px){
        #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-card { padding:15px 15px 17px; }
        #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-q { font-size:17px; }
        #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-face { padding:20px 17px; min-height:172px; }
        #rhfc-overlay .rhfc-keys { display:none; }
      }
    </style>

    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#0a6075;color:#fff;font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.04em;">RH</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Rheumatology</div>
        <div class="section-sub">The complete rheumatology resource &mdash; the playbook, the training room, the revenue estimator, and every file, ready to email</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rhsub-nav">
      <button type="button" class="rhsub-btn on" id="rhsub-playbook"  onclick="rheumShowView('playbook', this)">The Playbook</button>
      <button type="button" class="rhsub-btn"    id="rhsub-training"  onclick="rheumShowView('training', this)">Training</button>
      <button type="button" class="rhsub-btn" id="rhsub-pftsuite" onclick="rheumShowView('pftsuite', this)">PFT Suite</button>
      <button type="button" class="rhsub-btn"    id="rhsub-estimator" onclick="rheumShowView('estimator', this)">PFT Estimator</button>
      <button type="button" class="rhsub-btn"    id="rhsub-composer"  onclick="rheumShowView('composer', this)">Interp Composer</button>
      <button type="button" class="rhsub-btn"    id="rhsub-files"     onclick="rheumShowView('files', this)">Files &amp; Templates</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Rehearse the Room: full-screen act overlay (scenes rendered by rhActRender) -->
    <!-- The Whetstone: recall-drill overlay. Body rendered by rhfcRender() from RHFC_DECKS. -->
    <div id="rhfc-overlay" class="rhp" onclick="if(event.target===this)rhfcClose()">
      <div class="rhfc-card" id="rhfc-body"></div>
    </div>
    <!-- Where the six numbers come from. The answer to "…and what's a z-score?" -->
    <div id="rhrep-overlay" class="rhp" onclick="if(event.target===this)rhRepClose()">
      <div class="rhrep-card">
        <div class="rhrep-top">
          <div>
            <div class="rhrep-tag">The source document</div>
            <div class="rhrep-title">This is the report the numbers come off</div>
            <div class="rhrep-sub">The MiniBox+ prints this. Every box in the Composer is one number on this page &mdash; the six that matter are marked and numbered in the order the Composer asks for them. <b>Tap any marked row to drop it straight into the form.</b></div>
          </div>
          <button type="button" class="rhrep-x" onclick="rhRepClose()" aria-label="Close">&#10005;</button>
        </div>
        <div class="rhrep-body">
          <div class="rhrep-sheet">
            <div class="rhrep-head">
              <div>
                <div class="rhrep-brand">PulmOne MiniBox+</div>
                <div class="rhrep-kind">Pulmonary Function Test Report &middot; PFT Outside The Box</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rhrep-kind">Test date 03 / 14 / 2026</div>
            </div>
            <div class="rhrep-demo-note">DEMONSTRATION REPORT &mdash; sample values for training. Not a real patient.</div>
            <div class="rhrep-pt">
              <div><span>Patient</span><b>Demo, R.A.</b></div>
              <div><span>Age / Sex</span><b>58 &middot; Female</b></div>
              <div><span>Height</span><b>5&prime;5&Prime;</b></div>
              <div><span>Weight</span><b>251 lb</b></div>
              <div><span>BMI</span><b><span class="rhrep-pin">6</span>41.8</b></div>
              <div><span>Reference</span><b>NHANES III</b></div>
            </div>

            <div class="rhrep-sec">Spirometry &mdash; how much air, how fast</div>
            <table class="rhrep-t">
              <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Pred.</th><th>Best</th><th>%Pred</th><th>Z-score</th><th>Flag</th></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-use" onclick="rhRepPick('ratio')" title="Click to fill Gate 1 in the Composer">
                <td><span class="rhrep-pin">1</span>FEV<sub>1</sub>/FVC</td><td>81.1</td><td>83.5</td><td>103%</td>
                <td class="rhrep-z ok">+0.38</td><td><span class="rhrep-flag ok">NORMAL</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-use" onclick="rhRepPick('fvc')" title="Click to fill FVC in the Composer">
                <td><span class="rhrep-pin">4</span>FVC (L)</td><td>4.04</td><td>1.94</td><td>48%</td>
                <td class="rhrep-z low">&minus;4.55</td><td><span class="rhrep-flag low">&darr; LOW</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-use" onclick="rhRepPick('fev1')" title="Click to fill FEV1 in the Composer">
                <td><span class="rhrep-pin">5</span>FEV<sub>1</sub> (L)</td><td>3.24</td><td>1.62</td><td>50%</td>
                <td class="rhrep-z low">&minus;4.18</td><td><span class="rhrep-flag low">&darr; LOW</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-sec2"><td>FEF 25&ndash;75 (L/s)</td><td>3.30</td><td>2.05</td><td>62%</td><td class="rhrep-z">&minus;1.42</td><td></td></tr>
            </table>

            <div class="rhrep-sec">Lung volumes &mdash; how big are the lungs</div>
            <table class="rhrep-t">
              <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Pred.</th><th>Best</th><th>%Pred</th><th>Z-score</th><th>Flag</th></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-use" onclick="rhRepPick('tlc')" title="Click to fill Gate 2 in the Composer">
                <td><span class="rhrep-pin">2</span>TLC (L)</td><td>5.94</td><td>3.21</td><td>54%</td>
                <td class="rhrep-z low">&minus;3.78</td><td><span class="rhrep-flag low">&darr; LOW</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-sec2"><td>RV (L)</td><td>1.98</td><td>1.22</td><td>62%</td><td class="rhrep-z">&minus;1.55</td><td></td></tr>
            </table>

            <div class="rhrep-sec">Diffusion (DLCO) &mdash; is oxygen crossing over</div>
            <table class="rhrep-t">
              <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Pred.</th><th>Best</th><th>%Pred</th><th>Z-score</th><th>Flag</th></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-use" onclick="rhRepPick('dlco')" title="Click to fill Gate 3 in the Composer">
                <td><span class="rhrep-pin">3</span>DLCO corr.</td><td>17.40</td><td>9.40</td><td>54%</td>
                <td class="rhrep-z low">&minus;3.61</td><td><span class="rhrep-flag low">&darr; LOW</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="rhrep-sec2"><td>VA (L)</td><td>5.60</td><td>3.55</td><td>63%</td><td class="rhrep-z">&minus;1.48</td><td></td></tr>
            </table>
            <div style="height:12px"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="rhrep-clicknote" data-mbx-tip="rh-report-click">👆 Tap any numbered row above and it fills that box in the Composer &mdash; so you can see exactly which number lands where.</div>

          <div class="rhrep-z-explain">
            <h4>&ldquo;What&rsquo;s a Z-score?&rdquo; &mdash; the question you&rsquo;ll get</h4>
            <p><b>How many steps a value sits above or below the average healthy person</b> of the same age, height, sex and ethnicity. <b>0 means exactly predicted.</b> Anything below <b>&minus;1.645</b> counts as abnormal &mdash; that&rsquo;s the LLN line. A &minus;4 means &ldquo;far, far below normal.&rdquo;</p>
            <p>It&rsquo;s the modern ATS/ERS standard because <b>one number</b> tells you how far off a patient is, no matter which parameter you&rsquo;re looking at &mdash; and unlike &ldquo;80% of predicted,&rdquo; it already accounts for the fact that normal ranges differ by age and size.</p>
            <div class="rhrep-scale">
              <div class="rhrep-scale-bar"></div>
              <div class="rhrep-scale-lln"></div>
              <div class="rhrep-dot" style="left:15.3%"><b>TLC &minus;3.78</b></div>
              <div class="rhrep-dot" style="left:17.4%"></div>
              <div class="rhrep-dot ok" style="left:67.3%"><b>ratio +0.38</b></div>
              <div class="rhrep-scale-lbl" style="left:41.9%">LLN &minus;1.645</div>
              <div class="rhrep-scale-lbl" style="left:62.5%">predicted (0)</div>
            </div>
            <p style="margin-top:20px">That picture is the whole case in one line: <b>airflow sits in the normal zone, the lungs and the gas transfer are off the left edge.</b> Normal ratio, small lungs, low DLCO &mdash; restriction with a gas-exchange defect.</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom:0"><b>If the report has no Z-score column</b>, use the <b>% Predicted</b> column instead and the Composer falls back to the 80% rule. The z-score is better where you have it.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="rhrep-foot">
            <button type="button" class="rhc-btn" onclick="rhRepFillAll()"> Fill all six boxes from this report</button>
            <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="rhRepClose()">Close</button>
            <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="window.open('https://minibox-pft-suite.vercel.app','_blank')">Explore a live report &rarr;</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="rhact-overlay" class="rhp" onclick="if(event.target===this)rhActClose()">
      <div class="rhact-card" id="rhact-card"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ VIEW: PFT SUITE (embedded, stays in the toolkit) ============ -->
    <div id="rheum-view-pftsuite" style="display:none;">
      <div class="rhps-wrap">
        <div class="rhps-bar">
          <div>
            <div class="rhps-t">PFT Suite <span class="rhps-off">works offline</span></div>
            <div class="rhps-s" id="rhps-crumb">The Trainer and all six pattern pages, built into this toolkit.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rhps-btns">
            <button type="button" class="rhps-b ghost" id="rhps-back" style="display:none;" onclick="rhpsOpen('index.html')">&#8592; Suite menu</button>
            <button type="button" class="rhps-b" onclick="rhpsPopOut()">Open full screen <span style="font-size:11px;opacity:.85;">&#8599;</span></button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rhps-frame">
          <iframe id="rhps-iframe" title="MiniBox PFT Suite" allow="fullscreen"></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ VIEW: PLAYBOOK ============ -->
    <div id="rheum-view-playbook" class="rhp">
      <div class="rhp-files-cta">
        <div>
          <div class="rhp-files-cta-h"> The rheum pack &mdash; 7 files + 3 interactive tools</div>
          <div class="rhp-files-cta-s">Segment slick, field reference, training deck, ACR/CHEST guideline, patient fact sheet &amp; email templates &mdash; plus the Estimator, Billing Helper and Interp Composer as working copies.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rhp-files-cta-btns">
          <button type="button" onclick="rheumShowView('files', document.getElementById('rhsub-files'))">Open the files</button>
          <button type="button" class="ghost" onclick="rheumEmailAll()"> Email the pack</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rhp-lede">Everything for the rheumatology call in one place &mdash; the play, the numbers, the answers, and every file. Field-tested. Built for the team.</div>

      <!-- Training lives in its own view now. This is the quiet pointer to it. -->
      <div class="rhp-trainline">
        <div class="rhp-trainline-txt"><b>Reading it once isn&rsquo;t knowing it.</b> Sharpen the recall and rehearse the live room in <span class="rhp-trainline-em">Training</span>.</div>
        <button type="button" class="rhp-trainline-btn" onclick="rheumShowView('training', document.getElementById('rhsub-training'))">Open Training</button>
      </div>

      <div class="rhp-sec">
        <div class="rhp-sec-head"><span class="rhp-sec-num">01</span><span class="rhp-sec-title">The play, in five moves</span></div>
        <div class="rhp-steps rhp-drill" role="button" tabindex="0" title="Sharpen the five moves" onclick="rhfcStart('moves')" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'||event.key===' '){event.preventDefault();rhfcStart('moves');}">
          <div class="rhp-drill-tag">Drill &middot; 5</div>
          <div class="rhp-step"><div class="rhp-n">1</div><div><h4>Anchor on the guideline</h4><p>The 2023 ACR/CHEST guideline names PFTs &mdash; spirometry, lung volumes, and DLCO &mdash; as recommended for ILD screening and monitoring in RA, scleroderma, Sj&ouml;gren&rsquo;s, MCTD, and inflammatory myopathies. That&rsquo;s the door.</p></div></div>
          <div class="rhp-step"><div class="rhp-n">2</div><div><h4>Find the volume already in the chart</h4><p>A rheumatologist with high RA and SSc volume is already sending PFTs out the door. The population exists &mdash; they&rsquo;re just referring it out.</p></div></div>
          <div class="rhp-step"><div class="rhp-n">3</div><div><h4>Discover, don&rsquo;t pitch</h4><p>On the first call, ask the four questions (below). Let the rheumatologist do the math on owning their own DLCO data.</p></div></div>
          <div class="rhp-step"><div class="rhp-n">4</div><div><h4>Handle the three objections cleanly</h4><p>Staff training, reimbursement, and upfront cost. The answers are in Quick Reference &mdash; memorize them.</p></div></div>
          <div class="rhp-step"><div class="rhp-n">5</div><div><h4>Close on the financing that fits</h4><p>Lease-to-own with $0 down removes the capital objection. The clinical case carries the rest.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rhp-sec">
        <div class="rhp-sec-head"><span class="rhp-sec-num">02</span><span class="rhp-sec-title">The patient math</span></div>
        <div class="rhp-stats rhp-drill" role="button" tabindex="0" title="Sharpen the patient math" onclick="rhfcStart('numbers')" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'||event.key===' '){event.preventDefault();rhfcStart('numbers');}">
          <div class="rhp-drill-tag">Drill &middot; 3</div>
          <div class="rhp-stat"><div class="rhp-big">50%+</div><div class="rhp-lbl">of scleroderma (SSc) patients develop ILD</div></div>
          <div class="rhp-stat"><div class="rhp-big">10&ndash;30%</div><div class="rhp-lbl">of RA patients develop ILD</div></div>
          <div class="rhp-stat"><div class="rhp-big">DLCO</div><div class="rhp-lbl">most sensitive early marker for ILD &mdash; MiniBox+ runs it as part of a complete PFT, not a bolt-on</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rhp-sec">
        <div class="rhp-sec-head"><span class="rhp-sec-num">03</span><span class="rhp-sec-title">Quick reference</span></div>
        <div class="rhp-grid2">
          <div class="rhp-ref rhp-drill" role="button" tabindex="0" title="Sharpen the CPT bundle" onclick="rhfcStart('cpt')" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'||event.key===' '){event.preventDefault();rhfcStart('cpt');}">
            <div class="rhp-drill-tag">Drill &middot; 6</div>
            <h4>The CPT bundle</h4>
            <div class="rhp-cpt"><div class="rhp-cpt-code">94010</div><div class="rhp-cpt-desc">Spirometry with graphic record</div></div>
            <div class="rhp-cpt"><div class="rhp-cpt-code">94726</div><div class="rhp-cpt-desc">Plethysmography for lung volumes (TLC)</div></div>
            <div class="rhp-cpt"><div class="rhp-cpt-code">94729</div><div class="rhp-cpt-desc">Diffusing capacity (DLCO)</div></div>
            <div class="rhp-note"><b>Medical necessity lives in the documentation, not the code.</b> Document symptoms (dyspnea, cough, crackles) or the underlying diagnosis on the order. <span style="color:#8a6520;">94060 is spirometry <em>with</em> bronchodilator and already includes 94010 &mdash; never bill both.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="rhp-ref rhp-drill" role="button" tabindex="0" title="Sharpen the monitoring cadence" onclick="rhfcStart('cadence')" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'||event.key===' '){event.preventDefault();rhfcStart('cadence');}">
            <div class="rhp-drill-tag">Drill &middot; 5</div>
            <h4>Monitoring cadence (PFTs)</h4>
            <table class="rhp-mini">
              <tr><th>Disease</th><th>First year</th><th>Once stable</th></tr>
              <tr><td>SSc-ILD</td><td>Every 3&ndash;6 mo</td><td>Every 6&ndash;12 mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td>IIM-ILD</td><td>Every 3&ndash;6 mo</td><td>Every 6&ndash;12 mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td>RA-ILD</td><td>Every 3&ndash;12 mo</td><td>Every 6&ndash;12 mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td>SjD / MCTD-ILD</td><td>Every 3&ndash;12 mo</td><td>Every 6&ndash;12 mo</td></tr>
            </table>
            <div class="rhp-note">More frequent testing for progressive fibrotic phenotypes, treatment changes, or clinical deterioration. <b>Recurring PFTs = recurring utilization.</b></div>
          </div>
          <div class="rhp-ref rhp-drill" role="button" tabindex="0" title="Sharpen the three objections" onclick="if(!event.target.closest('button'))rhfcStart('objections')" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'||event.key===' '){event.preventDefault();rhfcStart('objections');}">
            <div class="rhp-drill-tag">Drill &middot; 3</div>
            <h4>The three objections</h4>
            <div class="rhp-obj"><div class="rhp-q">&ldquo;My staff isn&rsquo;t trained on PFTs.&rdquo;</div><div class="rhp-a">No RT required. We train the MA, RN, or NP &mdash; plus training, support, and return visits.</div></div>
            <div class="rhp-obj"><div class="rhp-q">&ldquo;Will I get reimbursed? I&rsquo;m a rheumatologist.&rdquo;</div><div class="rhp-a">Yes. The ACR/CHEST guideline gives clean medical-necessity documentation. Bundle: <b>94010 + 94726 + 94729</b>.<br><span style="font-size:11.5px;color:#8a8a8a;">Use 94010, not 94060, for ILD screening &mdash; 94060 is spirometry <em>with</em> bronchodilator and already includes 94010, so billing both denies as bundled. Bronchodilator response is an asthma/COPD question, not an ILD one. Full rules in the <button type="button" onclick="m3View('calc-pft-coding')" style="background:none;border:none;color:#0a6075;font-weight:700;text-decoration:underline;cursor:pointer;padding:0;font-size:inherit;">Billing Helper</button>.</span></div></div>
            <div class="rhp-obj"><div class="rhp-q">&ldquo;$15K upfront is a stretch.&rdquo;</div><div class="rhp-a">Lease-to-own, zero upfront. See financing options at right.</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="rhp-ref">
            <h4>Financing options</h4>
            <div class="rhp-fin"><div class="rhp-t">Lease-to-Own &mdash; $0 down</div><div class="rhp-d">12 / 24 / 36 / 60-month terms &middot; optional 90-day payment deferral &middot; $1 buyout at end of term.</div></div>
            <div class="rhp-fin"><div class="rhp-t">0% Financing &mdash; up to 12 months</div><div class="rhp-d">$7,500 at signing &middot; $7,500 at installation ($15,000 upfront) &middot; 0% on the balance over up to 12 equal monthly payments.</div></div>
            <div class="rhp-fin"><div class="rhp-t">Subscription</div><div class="rhp-d">Fixed monthly cost covers device use and filters. No large capital outlay.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rhp-sec">
        <div class="rhp-sec-head"><span class="rhp-sec-num">04</span><span class="rhp-sec-title">The four discovery questions</span></div>
        <div class="rhp-lede" style="margin-top:-6px;">Don&rsquo;t pitch on the discovery call. Ask. These are the four.</div>
        <div class="rhp-qs rhp-drill" role="button" tabindex="0" title="Sharpen the discovery questions" onclick="rhfcStart('discovery')" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'||event.key===' '){event.preventDefault();rhfcStart('discovery');}">
          <div class="rhp-drill-tag">Drill &middot; 4</div>
          <div class="rhp-qitem"><p>&ldquo;What percentage of your patients are on DMARDs or biologics, and how do you currently monitor them for pulmonary toxicity?&rdquo;</p></div>
          <div class="rhp-qitem"><p>&ldquo;For your RA and scleroderma patients, where are you sending PFTs today &mdash; and how long until you get the results back?&rdquo;</p></div>
          <div class="rhp-qitem"><p>&ldquo;When a patient&rsquo;s DLCO trends down, what does your workflow look like to catch it?&rdquo;</p></div>
          <div class="rhp-qitem rhp-closer"><p><span class="rhp-qtag">The closer</span><br>&ldquo;How would your treatment cadence change if you owned the PFT data inside your practice?&rdquo;</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rhp-sec">
        <div class="alert-box alert-blue" style="margin:0;">
          <div class="alert-icon"></div>
          <div><strong>Ready to send something?</strong> The seven rheumatology files and the three interactive tools &mdash; the segment slick, the ACR/CHEST guideline, the patient fact sheet, the training deck, and the email templates &mdash; are all in <button onclick="rheumShowView('files', document.getElementById('rhsub-files'))" style="background:none;border:none;color:#0a6075;font-weight:700;text-decoration:underline;cursor:pointer;padding:0;font-size:inherit;">Files &amp; Templates</button>. View, download, or email any of them with the file genuinely attached.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ VIEW: TRAINING ============ -->
    <div id="rheum-view-training" style="display:none;" class="rhp">
      <div class="rhtr-head">
        <div class="rhtr-kicker">Rheumatology &middot; Training</div>
        <h3 class="rhtr-h">Two ways to get it into your hands</h3>
        <p class="rhtr-s">The playbook is the reference. This is the practice. Sharpen the recall first, then take it into a room that pushes back.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rhtr-pair">
        <div class="rhtr-mod">
          <div class="rhtr-mod-n">01</div>
          <div class="rhtr-mod-h">The Whetstone</div>
          <div class="rhtr-mod-tag">Recall drills &middot; 6 decks &middot; 26 cards</div>
          <p class="rhtr-mod-s">The five moves, the patient math, the CPT bundle, the monitoring cadence, the three objections, the four discovery questions. Say the answer out loud, then flip. You don&rsquo;t finish a deck until you&rsquo;ve said every card right.</p>
          <div class="rhtr-mod-track" id="rhtr-track"></div>
          <button type="button" class="rhtr-mod-btn" onclick="rhfcOpen()">Take the stone</button>
        </div>
        <div class="rhtr-mod" id="rhtr-room">
          <div class="rhtr-mod-n">02</div>
          <div class="rhtr-mod-h">The Room</div>
          <div class="rhtr-mod-tag">Live rehearsal &middot; three voices</div>
          <p class="rhtr-mod-s">Three people stand between you and a signature: the owner who counts the capital, the biller who counts the denials, and the physician who counts the patients. Meet all three before you walk in, not during.</p>
          <div class="rhtr-mod-cast"><span>The owner</span><span>The biller</span><span>The physician</span></div>
          <button type="button" class="rhtr-mod-btn" onclick="rhActOpen()">Walk in</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rhtr-note">Everything drilled here is the same copy as the playbook &mdash; nothing new to learn, just moved from the page into your mouth.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ VIEW: ESTIMATOR ============ -->
    <div id="rheum-view-estimator" style="display:none;">
    <div class="alert-box alert-blue">
      <div class="alert-icon">&#9432;</div>
      <div><strong>How to use this with a rheumatologist:</strong> Walk through Section 1 (their confirmed ILD-risk patients), Section 2 (weekly symptom flow), and Section 3 (drug monitoring). The bottom bar shows annual PFT volume and revenue at $150 per panel &mdash; adjust for their payer mix. This is the single best discovery tool for a rheumatology practice.</div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:0 0 16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;"><button type="button" class="rhc-btn" onclick="m3EmailThis('calc-rheum')">&#9993; Send this estimator to a practice</button><span style="font-size:11.5px;color:#8a8a8a;">Goes as a working file &mdash; they open it in a browser and run their own numbers.</span></div>

    <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:flex-start;border:1px solid #e6c98a;border-left:5px solid #c98b1d;background:#fffaf0;border-radius:10px;padding:14px 17px;margin:0 0 16px;">
      <span style="font-size:18px;line-height:1;flex-shrink:0;"></span>
      <div style="font-size:12.5px;color:#5a5a5a;line-height:1.6;">
        <div style="font-size:13.5px;font-weight:800;color:#9a6510;margin-bottom:4px;">Screening vs. monitoring &mdash; know the difference before you promise revenue</div>
        Medicare policy states plainly that coverage <strong>&ldquo;excludes routine (screening) tests for asymptomatic patients with or without high risk of lung disease.&rdquo;</strong>
        The ACR/CHEST guideline recommends screening at-risk patients; Medicare does not pay for it. Both are true, and no policy reconciles them.
        <div style="margin-top:7px;"><strong>The line that works:</strong> a patient with <em>documented lung involvement or respiratory symptoms</em> is being <strong>monitored</strong> &mdash; that is diagnostic and payable.
        A truly asymptomatic patient with no established lung disease is being <strong>screened</strong> &mdash; that is patient-liable and needs an ABN.</div>
        <div style="margin-top:7px;">Count Section 1 honestly: only patients who clear the monitoring bar belong in a revenue projection. Coding a symptom a patient does not have, to force payment, is a False Claims Act problem &mdash; never suggest it.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rheum-est">
      <div class="rheum-card">

        <div class="rheum-top">
          <div>
            <div class="rheum-title-h">Rheumatology PFT Estimator</div>
            <div class="rheum-subtitle">Qualifying Diagnoses &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Symptom Pathways &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Drug Monitoring Codes</div>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align:right;">
            <div style="font-size:10px;color:#85B7EB;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;font-family:'SF Mono','Consolas',monospace;">PFT Revenue Tool</div>
            <div style="font-size:10px;color:#5d8fc5;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-top:4px;font-family:'SF Mono','Consolas',monospace;">94010 &middot; 94726 &middot; 94729</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rhl-hint">
          <span class="rhl-hint-ico">&#9432;</span>
          <div><b>Learn as you go:</b> every underlined term below &mdash; each diagnosis, symptom and drug &mdash; opens a plain-English card. Hover it on a laptop, tap it on a tablet. Each one tells you what the condition <i>is</i> and how it shows up on a lung function test.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-section-bar blue">
          <div class="rh-section-num blue">1</div>
          <div class="rh-section-title blue">Confirmed Diagnoses</div>
          <div class="rh-section-desc">&mdash; Recurring annual or semi-annual billing. Enter how many patients you have with each diagnosis.</div>
        </div>

        <div style="padding: 9px 20px 0; font-size: 11px; color: #777; background: #fafaf8; border-bottom: 0.5px solid #eeede8;">
          <strong style="color:#555;">Risk pills</strong> indicate likelihood of ILD development based on disease prevalence &mdash; they guide screening urgency, not billing frequency.
          Frequency reflects clinically supported billing cadence; Medicare reimburses when medical necessity is documented (no hard cap).
          <div style="margin-top:6px;padding-top:6px;border-top:1px dashed #e2e0d8;">
            <strong style="color:#555;">Coding the pair:</strong> use the <strong>&ldquo;with lung involvement&rdquo;</strong> form of the rheumatologic code (M34.81, M35.02, M32.13, M33.01/.11/.21) &mdash; the bare disease codes are absent from MAC covered-diagnosis lists.
            When ILD is established, add the manifestation code <strong>J84.170</strong> (progressive fibrotic phenotype) or <strong>J84.178</strong> (other ILD with fibrosis), and <strong>sequence the rheumatologic disease first</strong> &mdash; both J84.17x codes carry an explicit &ldquo;code first&rdquo; instruction. J84.17 alone is not billable.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th style="width:30%;">Qualifying Diagnosis</th>
                <th>ICD-10 Code(s)</th>
                <th>Bill With (CPT)</th>
                <th class="c-center">Typical<br>frequency</th>
                <th class="c-center">My pts</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell">
                  <div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="ssc">Systemic sclerosis (SSc)</span> <span class="rh-risk rh-risk-h">high</span></div>
                  <div class="rh-diag-drug">&#8595; On <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="cyc">cyclophosphamide</span> or <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="mmf">MMF</span> &rarr; up to 4x/yr</div>
                </div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M34.81</span><span class="rh-icd-pill">J84.178</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1&ndash;2x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">annual / semi-annual</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r1" data-freq="1.5" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell">
                  <div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="pmdm">Inflammatory myopathy &mdash; PM/DM</span> <span class="rh-risk rh-risk-h">high</span></div>
                  <div class="rh-diag-drug">&#8595; On <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="cyc">cyclophosphamide</span> &rarr; up to 4x/yr</div>
                </div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M33.11</span><span class="rh-icd-pill">M33.21</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1&ndash;2x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">annual / semi-annual</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r2" data-freq="1.5" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell">
                  <div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="antisynth">Antisynthetase syndrome</span> <span class="rh-risk rh-risk-h">high</span></div>
                  <div class="rh-diag-drug">&#8595; ILD often present at diagnosis &mdash; baseline then every 6 months</div>
                  <div style="font-size:10px;color:#999;margin-top:4px;font-style:italic;line-height:1.4;">No dedicated ICD-10 &mdash; combine the myositis code (M33.91) with an ILD code (J84.89).</div>
                </div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M33.91</span><span class="rh-icd-pill">J84.89</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">2x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">semi-annual</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r3" data-freq="2" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell">
                  <div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="ra">RA with pulmonary involvement</span> <span class="rh-risk rh-risk-m">mod</span></div>
                  <div class="rh-diag-drug">&#8595; On <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="mtx">methotrexate</span> or <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="leflunomide">leflunomide</span> &rarr; baseline PFT required; retest if symptoms arise</div>
                </div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M05.10</span><span class="rh-icd-pill">J84.89</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1&ndash;2x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">annual / as indicated</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r4" data-freq="1.5" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell"><div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="mctd">Mixed connective tissue disease</span> <span class="rh-risk rh-risk-m">mod</span></div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M35.1</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">annual</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r5" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell"><div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="sjogren">Sj&ouml;gren's with pulmonary involvement</span> <span class="rh-risk rh-risk-m">mod</span></div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M35.02</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">annual</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r6" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell"><div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="sle">SLE with respiratory involvement</span></div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M32.13</span><span class="rh-icd-pill">M32.19</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">as indicated</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r7" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><div class="cell"><div class="rh-diag-name"><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="anca">ANCA-associated vasculitis (GPA / MPA)</span></div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-icd-pill">M31.30</span><span class="rh-icd-pill">M31.7</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-freq-main">1x</div><div class="rh-freq-sub">annual / as indicated</div></div></td>
                <td><div class="cell" style="text-align:center;"><div class="rh-tally" contenteditable="true" data-rid="r8" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)">0</div></div></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-section-bar teal">
          <div class="rh-section-num teal">2</div>
          <div class="rh-section-title teal">Suspected ILD &mdash; Symptom Pathway</div>
          <div class="rh-section-desc">&mdash; No confirmed diagnosis needed. Any patient presenting with these symptoms qualifies for a diagnostic PFT today.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-symptom-body">
          <p class="rh-symptom-intro">If a patient walks in with any of the following and you have clinical suspicion for interstitial lung disease, you can order, perform, and bill for a PFT right now &mdash; before a diagnosis is confirmed.</p>

          <div class="rh-trigger-grid">
            <div class="rh-trigger-chip rh-learn" data-gloss="dyspnea">Shortness of breath / dyspnea</div>
            <div class="rh-trigger-chip rh-learn" data-gloss="cough">Chronic or unexplained cough</div>
            <div class="rh-trigger-chip rh-learn" data-gloss="exertion">Reduced exercise tolerance</div>
            <div class="rh-trigger-chip rh-learn" data-gloss="desat">Unexplained oxygen desaturation</div>
            <div class="rh-trigger-chip rh-learn" data-gloss="crackles">Bibasilar crackles on exam</div>
            <div class="rh-trigger-chip rh-learn" data-gloss="newsx">New respiratory symptoms on any immunosuppressant</div>
          </div>

          <div class="rh-symptom-row">
            <div class="rh-sym-block">
              <label>Primary symptom code(s)</label>
              <span class="rh-icd-pill">R06.00</span> <span style="font-size:11px;color:#888;">Dyspnea</span><br>
              <span class="rh-icd-pill" style="margin-top:5px;display:inline-block;">R05.3</span> <span style="font-size:11px;color:#888;">Chronic cough</span><br>
              <span class="rh-icd-pill" style="margin-top:5px;display:inline-block;">R05.9</span> <span style="font-size:11px;color:#888;">Cough, unspecified</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rh-sym-block">
              <label>Supporting diagnosis</label>
              <span style="font-size:12px;color:#555;line-height:1.5;display:block;">Add their known rheumatologic condition as a secondary ICD-10 &mdash; it establishes why you're concerned about ILD specifically.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="rh-sym-block">
              <label>Bill with (CPT)</label>
              <span class="rh-code-pill teal">94010</span>
              <span class="rh-code-pill teal">94726</span>
              <span class="rh-code-pill teal">94729</span>
              <p style="font-size:11px;color:#888;margin-top:6px;">Full diagnostic panel &mdash; billed once per episode</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rh-weekly-box">
            <div class="rh-weekly-left">
              <div class="rh-tally teal" contenteditable="true" data-rid="s1" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalcWeekly()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)" aria-label="Symptomatic patients per week">0</div>
              <div>
                <div class="rh-weekly-label">Patients per week presenting with breathing symptoms</div>
                <div class="rh-weekly-sub">Think about a typical week in your clinic &mdash; how many mention shortness of breath or a new cough?</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="rh-weekly-divider"></div>
            <div>
              <div class="rh-weekly-result-label">Annual PFTs from this group</div>
              <div class="rh-weekly-result-number" id="rheum-weekly-annual">0</div>
              <div class="rh-weekly-result-sub">patients/wk &times; 52 weeks</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rh-convert-note">
            <span style="font-size:16px;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:-1px;">&rarr;</span>
            <div><strong>If ILD is confirmed</strong> &mdash; that patient moves to Section 1 and becomes a recurring annual or semi-annual billing patient. One diagnostic visit today creates a long-term revenue relationship.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-section-bar amber">
          <div class="rh-section-num amber">3</div>
          <div class="rh-section-title amber">Drug Monitoring &mdash; How to Code It</div>
          <div class="rh-section-desc">&mdash; Patient is on a high-risk drug and you're concerned. Find your scenario, use those codes, add your count.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-drug-body">
          <p class="rh-drug-intro">The drug alone doesn't generate the billing code &mdash; but the combination of their diagnosis, the drug they're on, and your documented clinical concern does. Match the scenario below to the situation.</p>

          <div class="rh-emr-tip">
            <span style="flex-shrink:0;">&#9432;</span>
            <div><strong>Finding your count:</strong> Run a medication report in your EMR &mdash; search by drug name (methotrexate, cyclophosphamide, leflunomide, etc.) to pull every active patient on that drug. Most systems can do this in under two minutes. That number goes in the tally box below each scenario.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="rh-scenario-grid">

            <div class="rh-scenario-card s1">
              <div class="rh-scenario-head">
                <div class="rh-scenario-num">Scenario 1</div>
                <div class="rh-scenario-name">Routine monitoring &mdash; no symptoms</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rh-scenario-body">
                <p class="rh-scenario-trigger">Patient is on a high-risk drug (<span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="mtx">MTX</span>, <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="cyc">CYC</span>, <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="leflunomide">leflunomide</span>, <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="jak">JAK inhibitor</span>). No complaints. You want a baseline or periodic check.</p>
                <div class="rh-scenario-codes">
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Underlying Dx</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Z79.631</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Z79.630</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Z79.622</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Z79.620</span>
                </div>
                <p class="rh-scenario-note"><strong>Use the drug-specific code &mdash; not Z79.899.</strong> <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="mtx">Methotrexate</span> <b>Z79.631</b> &middot; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="cyc">cyclophosphamide</span> <b>Z79.630</b> &middot; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="jak">JAK inhibitor</span> <b>Z79.622</b> &middot; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="biologic">immunosuppressive biologic</span> <b>Z79.620</b> &middot; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="aza">azathioprine</span> or <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="mmf">MMF</span> <b>Z79.624</b>. Z79.899 is correct only where no specific code exists &mdash; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="leflunomide">leflunomide</span> and <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="hcq">hydroxychloroquine</span>.</p>
                <p class="rh-scenario-note" style="color:#9a6510;"><strong>The weakest of the three &mdash; say so honestly.</strong> A status code with no symptom and no established lung disease is a thin medical-necessity story. Routine PFT surveillance of the asymptomatic methotrexate patient is not supported by the evidence base, and the 2021 ACR RA guideline makes no such monitoring recommendation. Baseline testing in a patient with symptoms or known lung disease is defensible; a standing test-everyone protocol is not.</p>
                <div style="margin-top:8px;"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rh-scenario-tally">
                <div class="rh-tally amber" contenteditable="true" data-rid="d1" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)" aria-label="Scenario 1 patients">0</div>
                <div class="rh-scenario-tally-label">Patients on high-risk drugs, no symptoms yet &mdash; run your EMR medication report</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rh-scenario-card s2">
              <div class="rh-scenario-head">
                <div class="rh-scenario-num">Scenario 2</div>
                <div class="rh-scenario-name">Patient has symptoms on the drug</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rh-scenario-body">
                <p class="rh-scenario-trigger">Patient reports shortness of breath, new cough, or reduced tolerance since starting the drug. Stronger billing case &mdash; document the symptoms.</p>
                <div class="rh-scenario-codes">
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Underlying Dx</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Z79.6&ndash;</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">R06.00</span>
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">R05.3</span>
                </div>
                <p class="rh-scenario-note">Stack the symptom code on top of the monitoring code. Significantly strengthens medical necessity.</p>
                <div style="margin-top:8px;"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rh-scenario-tally">
                <div class="rh-tally amber" contenteditable="true" data-rid="d2" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)" aria-label="Scenario 2 patients">0</div>
                <div class="rh-scenario-tally-label">Patients on a drug who are currently reporting breathing symptoms</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rh-scenario-card s3">
              <div class="rh-scenario-head">
                <div class="rh-scenario-num">Scenario 3</div>
                <div class="rh-scenario-name">Drug toxicity suspected</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rh-scenario-body">
                <p class="rh-scenario-trigger">You believe the drug may be causing lung damage &mdash; drug-induced pneumonitis or interstitial changes on imaging. Act now.</p>
                <div class="rh-scenario-codes">
                  <span class="rh-icd-pill">Underlying Dx</span>
                  <span class="rh-code-pill red">T45.1X5A</span>
                  <span class="rh-code-pill red">J70.2</span>
                  <span class="rh-code-pill red">J70.3</span>
                </div>
                <p class="rh-scenario-note">T45.1X5A = adverse effect of immunosuppressants. J70.2 acute / J70.3 chronic drug-induced pneumonitis.</p>
                <div style="margin-top:8px;"><span class="rh-code-pill">94010</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94726</span><span class="rh-code-pill">94729</span></div>
              </div>
              <div class="rh-scenario-tally">
                <div class="rh-tally amber" contenteditable="true" data-rid="d3" data-freq="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" onblur="rheumClean(this)" onfocus="rheumSel(this)" aria-label="Scenario 3 patients">0</div>
                <div class="rh-scenario-tally-label">Patients where you currently suspect drug-induced lung injury</div>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-revenue-bar">
          <div class="rh-rev-block">
            <div class="rh-rev-label">Total PFTs this year</div>
            <div class="rh-rev-number" id="rheum-total-pfts">0</div>
            <div class="rh-rev-sub" id="rheum-total-sub">Enter counts above to calculate</div>
            <div id="rheum-total-breakdown" style="font-size:10px;color:#aaa;margin-top:6px;line-height:1.5;font-family:'SF Mono','Consolas',monospace;letter-spacing:0.02em;">Confirmed: 0 &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Symptomatic: 0 &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Drug: 0</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rh-rev-block">
            <div class="rh-rev-label">Estimated annual revenue</div>
            <div class="rh-rev-number green" id="rheum-rev-estimate">$0</div>
            <div class="rh-rev-sub">Sections 1 + 2 + 3 combined</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rh-rev-block">
            <div class="rh-rev-label">Rate per PFT panel</div>
            <div class="rh-rev-rate-row">
              <label>$</label>
              <input class="rh-rev-rate-input" type="number" id="rheum-rate-input" value="150" min="1" oninput="rheumCalc()" aria-label="Dollars per PFT panel" />
              <span style="font-size:10px;color:#bbb;">adjust for your payer mix</span>
            </div>
            <div style="font-size:10px;color:#bbb;margin-top:8px;line-height:1.6;">94010 + 94726 + 94729<br>&asymp; $140&ndash;165 recent Medicare national average</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rh-card-footer">
          <div class="rh-footer-grid">
            <div class="rh-footer-block">
              <label>CPT Code Key</label>
              <p>94010 Spirometry (FVC, FEV1) &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; 94726 Plethysmography / lung volumes <em>(or 94727 if your lab uses gas dilution / washout)</em> &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; 94729 DLCO / diffusing capacity &mdash; <strong>add-on only</strong>, must accompany 94010 or 94726/94727</p>
              <p style="margin-top:7px;"><strong>Not 94060 for ILD.</strong> 94060 is spirometry <em>with</em> bronchodilator &mdash; a reversible-obstruction test. NCCI pairs it with 94010 at <strong>modifier indicator 0</strong>, meaning no modifier will ever unbundle them; billing both is a hard denial. The ACR/CHEST ILD guideline never mentions bronchodilator testing. Two further consequences worth knowing: 94060 carries <strong>direct</strong> supervision (a physician must be in the office suite), while 94010, 94726, 94727 and 94729 need only <strong>general</strong> supervision &mdash; so the correct ILD panel is also the easier one to staff.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rh-footer-block">
              <label>Section 3 ICD-10 Key</label>
              <p>Z79.631 Methotrexate &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Z79.630 Cyclophosphamide &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Z79.622 JAK inhibitor &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Z79.620 Immunosuppressive biologic &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Z79.624 Azathioprine / MMF &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Z79.899 <em>only</em> where no specific code exists (leflunomide, hydroxychloroquine) &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; R06.00 Dyspnea &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; R05.3 Chronic cough &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; T45.1X5A Adverse effect of immunosuppressive drugs &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; J70.2 Acute / J70.3 Chronic drug-induced interstitial pneumonitis</p>
              <p style="margin-top:7px;"><em>The Z79.6&ndash; drug-class family replaced Z79.899 for these agents effective 1 October 2022. If a claim still carries Z79.899 for methotrexate, it is three years out of date. When the drug has actually caused lung injury, sequence the manifestation first (J70.2 / J70.3) and the adverse-effect code second (T45.1X5A).</em></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="rh-footer-legal">Reimbursement estimates based on Medicare national averages (CY2026 national unadjusted: 94010 $29.73 + 94726 $63.80 + 94729 $63.46 = <strong>$156.99</strong>). Rates vary by geography, MAC, payer, and year &mdash; verify current rates before billing.
          Medicare reimburses based on documented medical necessity; there is no national frequency cap on PFTs, but repeat testing must be justified by documented clinical change, and routine testing at every office visit is expressly not reimbursable.
          Note that the standalone Medicare PFT coverage policies (LCD L34247 / article A57216) were <strong>retired in November 2023</strong> and folded into the Respiratory Care policy &mdash; frequency figures still circulating from those documents are obsolete. Several MAC jurisdictions, including New York, now have no PFT-specific policy at all, which means no covered-diagnosis list to fail and no safe harbour either.
          Every study requires a signed written interpretation; a computer-generated report needs a physician signature attesting to review and accuracy. Coverage excludes routine screening of asymptomatic patients.
          This tool is for planning and educational purposes only and is not coding, billing, legal, or compliance advice &mdash; verify against your own MAC and payer policies, and have a certified coder review before use in a live practice.</div>
        </div>

      </div>
      <div class="rhx" id="rhx-estimator" style="margin-top:16px;"></div>
    </div>
    </div><!-- end rheum-view-estimator -->

    <!-- ============ VIEW: INTERPRETATION COMPOSER ============ -->
    <div id="rheum-view-composer" style="display:none;">
      <div class="alert-box alert-blue">
        <div class="alert-icon">&#9432;</div>
        <div><strong>What this answers:</strong> &ldquo;Can my rheumatologists write a reimbursable interpretation without becoming pulmonologists?&rdquo; Enter the numbers off the MiniBox+ report, watch the same decision tree the device uses classify the pattern, and get a signature-ready draft. Start the timer and let them watch the clock &mdash; that is the demo.</div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin:0 0 16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;"><button type="button" class="rhc-btn" onclick="m3EmailThis('calc-interp')">&#9993; Send this composer to a practice</button><span style="font-size:11.5px;color:#8a8a8a;">Goes as a working file &mdash; the physician opens it in a browser and drafts on their own numbers.</span></div>

      <div class="rhc">
        <div class="rhc-card">
          <div class="rhc-head">
            <div>
              <h3> Interpretation Composer</h3>
              <p>ATS/ERS pattern logic &middot; LLN &amp; z-score based &middot; signature-ready draft</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="rhc-timer" id="rhc-timer">0:00</div>
              <span class="rhc-timer-lbl" id="rhc-timer-lbl">time to signature</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rhc-body">
            <div class="rhc-steps">

              <!-- STEP 1 -->
              <div>
                <div class="rhc-step-h">
                  <div class="rhc-step-n">1</div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="rhc-step-t">Type in what the report says</div>
                    <div class="rhc-step-s">Copy the numbers straight off the MiniBox+ report: the <b><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="zscore">Z-score</span></b> column if it has one (usually a negative number, like &minus;2.31), otherwise the <b><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="pctpred">% Predicted</span></b> column. One box per row is enough &mdash; just type the number. Not sure what it should look like, or what a Z-score even is? Hit <b> See the report these come from</b> below &mdash; it shows the actual MiniBox+ printout with these six numbers marked, and you can tap any one of them to drop it straight in here.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhl-hint" style="margin:0 0 12px;border-radius:9px;border:0.5px solid #d8ecf2;">
                  <span class="rhl-hint-ico">&#9432;</span>
                  <div><b>Don't know the term?</b> Every underlined word here &mdash; <i>Z-score</i>, <i>LLN</i>, <i>DL<sub>CO</sub></i>, <i>restriction</i> &mdash; opens a plain-English card. These are the exact words a rheumatologist will stop you on, so the answer is one tap away mid-conversation.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-vals">
                  <div class="rhc-val">
                    <label><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="ratio">FEV<sub>1</sub>/FVC ratio</span></label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">Gate 1 &mdash; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="obstruction">obstruction</span></span>
                    <div class="rhc-val-row">
                      <input type="number" step="0.01" id="rhc-ratio-z" placeholder="z-score" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">z</span>
                      <input type="number" step="0.1" id="rhc-ratio-p" placeholder="% pred" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">% pred</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="rhc-val-warn" id="rhc-ratio-warn"></div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-val">
                    <label><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="tlc">TLC</span></label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">Gate 2 &mdash; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="restriction">restriction</span></span>
                    <div class="rhc-val-row">
                      <input type="number" step="0.01" id="rhc-tlc-z" placeholder="z-score" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">z</span>
                      <input type="number" step="0.1" id="rhc-tlc-p" placeholder="% pred" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">% pred</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-val">
                    <label><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="dlco">DL<sub>CO</sub> (corrected)</span></label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">Gate 3 &mdash; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="gasexchange">gas exchange</span></span>
                    <div class="rhc-val-row">
                      <input type="number" step="0.01" id="rhc-dlco-z" placeholder="z-score" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">z</span>
                      <input type="number" step="0.1" id="rhc-dlco-p" placeholder="% pred" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">% pred</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-val">
                    <label><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="fvc">FVC</span></label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">supporting</span>
                    <div class="rhc-val-row">
                      <input type="number" step="0.01" id="rhc-fvc-z" placeholder="z-score" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">z</span>
                      <input type="number" step="0.1" id="rhc-fvc-p" placeholder="% pred" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">% pred</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-val">
                    <label><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="fev1">FEV<sub>1</sub></span></label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">grades <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="severity">severity</span></span>
                    <div class="rhc-val-row">
                      <input type="number" step="0.01" id="rhc-fev1-z" placeholder="z-score" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">z</span>
                      <input type="number" step="0.1" id="rhc-fev1-p" placeholder="% pred" oninput="rhcRun()">
                      <span class="rhc-val-tag">% pred</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-val">
                    <label><span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="bmi">BMI</span></label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">optional &mdash; triggers the obesity check</span>
                    <div class="rhc-val-row">
                      <input type="number" step="0.1" id="rhc-bmi" placeholder="kg/m&sup2;" oninput="rhcRun()">
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-btnrow">
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" id="rhc-demo-btn" onclick="rhcDemoToggle()"> Load the ILD demo case</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="rhRepOpen()"> See the report these come from</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="rhcClear()">Clear</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="rhcTimerToggle()" id="rhc-timer-btn"> Start timer</button>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-demo" id="rhc-demo-card">
                  <div class="rhc-demo-h">
                    <span class="rhc-demo-tag">Demo case</span>
                    <span class="rhc-demo-t">RA patient on methotrexate, new shortness of breath</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-demo-d">
                    These are the numbers off a real MiniBox+ report. The lungs move air fine &mdash; the <b>ratio is normal</b> &mdash; but the lungs are <b>small</b> (TLC 54% predicted) and <b>gas transfer is down</b> (DLCO 54% predicted). BMI is 41.8, so the tool also raises the obesity question, because body habitus can shrink lung volumes on its own.
                    <br><br>
                    <b>What it should land on:</b> restriction with a reduced DLCO &mdash; the pattern that points at an interstitial lung process, which is exactly what you&rsquo;re watching for in a connective-tissue-disease patient. Scroll down and the tree, the flags, and the finished paragraph all follow from these six numbers.
                    <br><br>
                    Press the button again to take the demo back out and put your own numbers in.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- STEP 2 -->
              <div>
                <div class="rhc-step-h">
                  <div class="rhc-step-n">2</div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="rhc-step-t">The tree does the classifying</div>
                    <div class="rhc-step-s">Same three gates, same order, as the chart printed on the MiniBox+ report.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-gates">
                  <div class="rhc-gate" id="rhc-g1">
                    <div class="rhc-gate-n">Gate 1 &middot; Airflow</div>
                    <div class="rhc-gate-q">FEV<sub>1</sub>/FVC &ge; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="lln">LLN</span>?</div>
                    <div class="rhc-gate-a" id="rhc-g1a">&mdash;</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-gate" id="rhc-g2">
                    <div class="rhc-gate-n">Gate 2 &middot; Size</div>
                    <div class="rhc-gate-q">TLC &ge; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="lln">LLN</span>?</div>
                    <div class="rhc-gate-a" id="rhc-g2a">&mdash;</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-gate" id="rhc-g3">
                    <div class="rhc-gate-n">Gate 3 &middot; Gas exchange</div>
                    <div class="rhc-gate-q">DL<sub>CO</sub> &ge; <span class="rh-learn" data-gloss="lln">LLN</span>?</div>
                    <div class="rhc-gate-a" id="rhc-g3a">&mdash;</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-verdict" id="rhc-verdict" style="margin-top:12px;">
                  <div class="rhc-verdict-lbl">Pattern</div>
                  <div class="rhc-verdict-v" id="rhc-verdict-v">Enter values to classify</div>
                  <div class="rhc-verdict-sev" id="rhc-verdict-sev" style="display:none;">
                    Severity:
                    <select id="rhc-sev" onchange="rhcCompose()">
                      <option>Mild</option><option>Moderate</option><option>Moderately severe</option><option>Severe</option><option>Very severe</option>
                    </select>
                    <span style="font-size:11px;color:#999;margin-left:6px;">graded on FEV<sub>1</sub> %pred &mdash; confirm against the report</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div id="rhc-flags"></div>
              </div>

              <!-- STEP 3 -->
              <div>
                <div class="rhc-step-h">
                  <div class="rhc-step-n">3</div>
                  <div>
                    <div class="rhc-step-t">Sign the draft</div>
                    <div class="rhc-step-s">Type the name and date below and they drop into the bottom of the draft. Edit the text freely &mdash; the bracketed prompts are where the rheumatologist adds the clinical context only they have.</div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-sign">
                  <div class="rhc-sign-f">
                    <label>Interpreted by</label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">name and credentials &mdash; goes on the signature line</span>
                    <input type="text" id="rhc-signer" placeholder="Jane Rivera, MD" oninput="rhcCompose()">
                  </div>
                  <div class="rhc-sign-f">
                    <label>Date</label>
                    <span class="rhc-hint">defaults to today</span>
                    <input type="date" id="rhc-signdate" oninput="rhcCompose()">
                  </div>
                </div>
                <textarea class="rhc-out" id="rhc-out" placeholder="The draft interpretation appears here once a pattern is classified."></textarea>
                <div class="rhc-btnrow">
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn" onclick="rhcCopy()"> Copy interpretation</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn" onclick="rhcPrint()"> Print / save as PDF</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="rhcCompose()"> Regenerate draft</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="m3View('calc-pft-coding')"> Now how do I bill it? &rarr;</button>
                  <button type="button" class="rhc-btn ghost" onclick="rheumShowView('pftsuite', document.getElementById('rhsub-pftsuite'))"> Teach them to read it &mdash; PFT Suite &rarr;</button>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-where">
                  <div></div>
                  <div><b>Where does &ldquo;Copy&rdquo; put it?</b> On your clipboard &mdash; nothing is sent anywhere and nothing is saved here. Click into the patient&rsquo;s chart in your EMR and paste with <b>Ctrl&#8202;+&#8202;V</b> (<b>&#8984;&#8202;+&#8202;V</b> on a Mac). Copying is only how you carry the text over; if you&rsquo;d rather put a signed page in the file or hand one to the patient, use <b>Print / save as PDF</b> instead. In a demo, Copy is also what stops the clock.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="rhc-note">
                  <strong>Use it honestly:</strong> this is a drafting aid built on ATS/ERS pattern logic, not a diagnosis. Every interpretation requires physician review and signature &mdash; the same standard the MiniBox+ report itself states. Quality/acceptability of the maneuvers is the interpreting physician&rsquo;s call.
                </div>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rhx" id="rhx-composer"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="rhc-toast" id="rhc-toast">Copied</div>
    </div><!-- end rheum-view-composer -->

    <!-- ============ VIEW: FILES & TEMPLATES ============ -->
    <div id="rheum-view-files" style="display:none;" class="rhp">
      <div class="rhp-lede">Seven field-tested files for the rheumatology call, plus the three interactive tools as working copies you can send. <strong>View</strong> reads it, <strong>Download</strong> saves it, <strong>Email it</strong> jumps to the Email Center with the file genuinely attached &mdash; no manual attaching.</div>
      <div style="margin:14px 0;">
        <button class="eas-web-btn" style="background:#0a6075;" onclick="rheumEmailAll()" title="Loads the 7 rheumatology files + 3 interactive tools into the Email Center as attachments"> Email the whole rheum pack</button>
      </div>
      <div id="rheum-files-grid"><!-- rendered by toolkit v3 engine --></div>
    </div>

    <script>
      var rheumDiagRows = [
        {id:'r1',freq:1.5},{id:'r2',freq:1.5},{id:'r3',freq:2},
        {id:'r4',freq:1.5},{id:'r5',freq:1},{id:'r6',freq:1},
        {id:'r7',freq:1},{id:'r8',freq:1}
      ];
      var rheumDrugRows = [{id:'d1',freq:1},{id:'d2',freq:1},{id:'d3',freq:1}];

      function rheumGetN(id) {
        var el = document.querySelector('#tab-rheum [data-rid="' + id + '"]');
        if (!el) return 0;
        var v = parseInt(el.textContent.trim());
        return isNaN(v) || v < 0 ? 0 : v;
      }

      function rheumCalcWeekly() {
        var wk = rheumGetN('s1');
        var annual = wk * 52;
        var el = document.getElementById('rheum-weekly-annual');
        if (el) el.textContent = annual;
        rheumCalc();
      }

      function rheumCalc() {
        var s1Total = 0, s2Total = 0, s3Total = 0;
        for (var i = 0; i < rheumDiagRows.length; i++) {
          s1Total += rheumGetN(rheumDiagRows[i].id) * rheumDiagRows[i].freq;
        }
        s2Total = rheumGetN('s1') * 52;
        for (var j = 0; j < rheumDrugRows.length; j++) {
          s3Total += rheumGetN(rheumDrugRows[j].id) * rheumDrugRows[j].freq;
        }
        var total = Math.round(s1Total + s2Total + s3Total);
        var rateEl = document.getElementById('rheum-rate-input');
        var rate = rateEl ? (parseFloat(rateEl.value) || 150) : 150;
        var rev = total * rate;

        var totalEl = document.getElementById('rheum-total-pfts');
        var subEl = document.getElementById('rheum-total-sub');
        var brkEl = document.getElementById('rheum-total-breakdown');
        var revEl = document.getElementById('rheum-rev-estimate');
        if (totalEl) totalEl.textContent = total;
        if (subEl) subEl.textContent = total === 0 ? 'Enter counts above to calculate' : 'visits / year across all three sections';
        if (brkEl) brkEl.textContent = 'Confirmed: ' + Math.round(s1Total) + '  ·  Symptomatic: ' + Math.round(s2Total) + '  ·  Drug: ' + Math.round(s3Total);
        if (revEl) revEl.textContent = '$' + Math.round(rev).toLocaleString();
      }

      function rheumSel(el) {
        if (el.textContent.trim() === '0') el.textContent = '';
        setTimeout(function() {
          var r = document.createRange();
          r.selectNodeContents(el);
          var s = window.getSelection();
          s.removeAllRanges();
          s.addRange(r);
        }, 0);
      }

      function rheumClean(el) {
        var v = parseInt(el.textContent.trim());
        el.textContent = isNaN(v) || v < 0 ? '0' : String(v);
        if (el.dataset.rid === 's1') { rheumCalcWeekly(); } else { rheumCalc(); }
      }

      document.querySelectorAll('#tab-rheum .rh-tally').forEach(function(el) {
        el.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
          if (e.key === 'Enter') { e.preventDefault(); this.blur(); }
          if (!/^[0-9]$|Backspace|Delete|Tab|ArrowLeft|ArrowRight/.test(e.key)) e.preventDefault();
        });
      });
    </script>

    <!-- ═══════════ LEARN LAYER: hover/tap any term ═══════════ -->
    <style id="rhl-style">
      #tab-rheum .rh-learn { cursor:help; border-bottom:1px dashed rgba(13,138,166,.6); color:inherit; transition:background .13s ease, border-color .13s ease; border-radius:3px; }
      #tab-rheum .rh-learn::after { content:'\24D8'; font-size:.82em; color:#0d8aa6; margin-left:3px; opacity:.65; vertical-align:baseline; }
      #tab-rheum .rh-learn:hover, #tab-rheum .rh-learn.rhl-on { background:rgba(13,138,166,.1); border-bottom-color:#0d8aa6; }
      #tab-rheum .rh-learn:hover::after, #tab-rheum .rh-learn.rhl-on::after { opacity:1; }
      #tab-rheum .rh-trigger-chip.rh-learn { border-bottom:0.5px solid #9FE1CB; }
      #tab-rheum .rh-trigger-chip.rh-learn:hover, #tab-rheum .rh-trigger-chip.rh-learn.rhl-on { background:#c9efe1; border-color:#4bbd97; }
      #tab-rheum .rh-scenario-note .rh-learn::after, #tab-rheum .rh-diag-drug .rh-learn::after { font-size:.78em; }

      #tab-rheum .rhl-hint { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:9px; padding:9px 20px; background:#f2fafc; border-bottom:0.5px solid #d8ecf2; font-size:11.5px; color:#3a5567; line-height:1.45; }
      #tab-rheum .rhl-hint b { color:#0a6075; }
      #tab-rheum .rhl-hint-ico { flex-shrink:0; font-size:14px; color:#0d8aa6; }

      #rhl-pop { position:fixed; z-index:9000; width:355px; max-width:calc(100vw - 24px); background:#fff; border:1px solid #cfe6ec; border-radius:13px; box-shadow:0 14px 44px rgba(14,42,58,.19), 0 2px 7px rgba(14,42,58,.09); display:none; overflow:hidden; font-family:inherit; }
      #rhl-pop.rhl-show { display:block; animation:rhlIn .14s ease-out; }
      @keyframes rhlIn { from { opacity:0; transform:translateY(5px); } to { opacity:1; transform:none; } }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-head { padding:13px 16px 11px; background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0d8aa6,#0a6075); position:relative; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-cat { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono','Consolas',monospace; font-size:9px; letter-spacing:.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9fdcea; margin-bottom:4px; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-term { font-size:15px; font-weight:800; color:#fff; line-height:1.25; letter-spacing:-.01em; padding-right:22px; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-x { position:absolute; top:9px; right:10px; width:21px; height:21px; border:0; border-radius:50%; background:rgba(255,255,255,.16); color:#fff; font-size:14px; line-height:1; cursor:pointer; padding:0; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-x:hover { background:rgba(255,255,255,.3); }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-body { padding:13px 16px 14px; max-height:56vh; overflow-y:auto; box-sizing:border-box; overscroll-behavior:contain; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-lbl { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono','Consolas',monospace; font-size:9.5px; letter-spacing:.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c98a2b; margin-bottom:5px; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:5px; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-lbl.pulm { color:#0d8aa6; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-txt { font-size:12.5px; color:#3a5567; line-height:1.62; margin:0 0 13px; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-txt:last-child { margin-bottom:0; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-txt b { color:#0e2a3a; font-weight:700; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-pulm-box { background:#eaf5f8; border-left:3px solid #0d8aa6; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0; padding:10px 12px; margin-bottom:11px; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-pulm-box .rhl-txt { margin:0; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-watch { display:flex; gap:7px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:11.5px; color:#7a5a12; background:#fdf6e6; border:1px solid #f0e2bf; border-radius:8px; padding:8px 10px; line-height:1.5; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-watch b { color:#5e440c; }
      #rhl-pop .rhl-foot { border-top:1px dashed #e2e0d8; padding:9px 16px 11px; font-size:10.5px; color:#8b9aa5; line-height:1.45; }
      @media (max-width:640px) {
        #rhl-pop { width:auto; left:10px !important; right:10px; bottom:10px !important; top:auto !important; max-width:none; }
        #rhl-pop .rhl-body { max-height:46vh; }
      }
    </style>

    <div id="rhl-pop" role="dialog" aria-live="polite">
      <div class="rhl-head">
        <div class="rhl-cat" id="rhl-cat"></div>
        <div class="rhl-term" id="rhl-term"></div>
        <button class="rhl-x" onclick="rhlClose(true)" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
      </div>
      <div class="rhl-body" id="rhl-body"></div>
      <div class="rhl-foot">Teaching reference for rep conversations &mdash; not clinical guidance or a diagnostic aid.</div>
    </div>

    <script id="rhl-script">
    (function(){
      var G = {
        ssc: { c:'Connective tissue disease', t:'Systemic sclerosis (scleroderma)',
          w:"An autoimmune disease that drives the body to lay down too much collagen &mdash; scar tissue &mdash; in the skin and internal organs. Typical patient has tight, shiny skin over the fingers and Raynaud's (fingers blanching white in the cold). The same scarring process reaches the lung.",
          p:"<b>The highest ILD risk in this entire list</b> &mdash; roughly 4 in 10 develop it, and lung disease is now the leading cause of death in scleroderma. It reads as a <b>restrictive</b> pattern: FVC and TLC fall while the FEV&#8321;/FVC ratio stays normal or even rises. <b>DLCO usually drops first</b>, often before the patient feels anything and before FVC has moved.",
          watch:"This is the case that makes the argument for the full panel: spirometry alone can read normal while the DLCO is already falling." },

        pmdm: { c:'Inflammatory muscle disease', t:'Inflammatory myopathy (PM / DM)',
          w:"Autoimmune inflammation of muscle. Patients present with weakness in the large proximal muscles &mdash; trouble climbing stairs or lifting arms overhead. Dermatomyositis adds a characteristic rash; polymyositis does not.",
          p:"Two <i>different</i> lung problems here, and the PFT is what separates them. <b>(1) True ILD</b> &mdash; restrictive with a low DLCO. <b>(2) Respiratory muscle weakness</b> &mdash; the diaphragm and chest wall are muscles too, so the same disease weakens the bellows. That also looks restrictive on spirometry, but the <b>DLCO is preserved</b> and mouth pressures (MIP/MEP) are reduced.",
          watch:"Low FVC with a <i>normal</i> DLCO points to weak bellows, not scarred lung &mdash; completely different treatment." },

        antisynth: { c:'Myositis subtype', t:'Antisynthetase syndrome',
          w:"A specific myositis subtype defined by antibodies against tRNA synthetase enzymes (anti-Jo-1 is the common one). Classic picture: muscle inflammation + ILD + arthritis + \"mechanic's hands\" (cracked, roughened finger skin) + Raynaud's + fever.",
          p:"<b>The one where the lung often comes first.</b> ILD is present at diagnosis in the majority of these patients, and in some the lung is the only organ involved at all. Restrictive physiology with a reduced DLCO. Because lung disease is a <i>defining feature</i> rather than a late complication, baseline at diagnosis then every 6 months is the standard rhythm.",
          watch:"Not a screening question &mdash; testing here is monitoring established disease, which is the stronger medical-necessity story." },

        ra: { c:'Connective tissue disease', t:'RA with pulmonary involvement',
          w:"Rheumatoid arthritis is autoimmune inflammation of the joint lining &mdash; symmetric swelling of the small joints of hands and feet, with morning stiffness. It is by far the most common disease on this list, so even a modest ILD rate produces a large number of patients.",
          p:"<b>RA hits the lung in more ways than anything else here, and each has a different PFT signature.</b> ILD &rarr; restrictive, low DLCO. Bronchiolitis obliterans (small-airway scarring) &rarr; <b>obstructive</b>, low FEV&#8321;/FVC. Bronchiectasis &rarr; obstructive. Pleural disease &rarr; restrictive.",
          watch:"You cannot predict which pattern you'll find &mdash; which is exactly why a symptomatic RA patient needs the full panel, not just spirometry." },

        mctd: { c:'Overlap syndrome', t:'Mixed connective tissue disease',
          w:"An overlap syndrome &mdash; features of lupus, scleroderma and myositis in one patient, tied together by high-titre anti-U1-RNP antibodies. Swollen \"sausage\" fingers and Raynaud's are typical.",
          p:"Because it borrows from scleroderma, it borrows scleroderma's lung risk: ILD is common, restrictive, with a reduced DLCO. MCTD also carries a real risk of <b>pulmonary hypertension</b>, which looks completely different &mdash; the DLCO falls <i>out of proportion</i> to the lung volumes, so you see an isolated low DLCO alongside a normal FVC and TLC.",
          watch:"That mismatch &mdash; low DLCO, normal volumes &mdash; is the finding that should prompt an echocardiogram." },

        sjogren: { c:'Connective tissue disease', t:"Sj&ouml;gren's with pulmonary involvement",
          w:"Autoimmune destruction of the moisture-producing glands &mdash; dry eyes and dry mouth are the hallmark. The same process dries and inflames the lining of the airways.",
          p:"Two patterns. The airways dry out and small-airway disease produces <b>obstruction</b>; separately, true ILD produces <b>restriction</b> with a low DLCO. A dry persistent cough in a Sj&ouml;gren's patient is almost always attributed to the dryness itself.",
          watch:"PFTs are how you tell nuisance dryness from developing lung disease &mdash; the symptom alone won't do it." },

        sle: { c:'Connective tissue disease', t:'SLE with respiratory involvement',
          w:"Lupus &mdash; an autoimmune disease that can inflame almost any organ and runs in flares. Joint pain, rashes, and kidney disease are the common threads.",
          p:"Classic ILD is <i>less</i> common in lupus than in scleroderma, but the lung is involved often. Most frequently that is pleurisy and pleural effusions, which restrict expansion mechanically. Lupus also produces <b>shrinking lung syndrome</b> &mdash; small measured lungs with a preserved DLCO, because the diaphragm isn't working. Restriction without scarring.",
          watch:"Lupus is also a leading cause of pulmonary hypertension in this group, so an isolated low DLCO carries weight." },

        anca: { c:'Small-vessel vasculitis', t:'ANCA-associated vasculitis (GPA / MPA)',
          w:"Autoimmune inflammation of the small blood vessels, driven by ANCA antibodies. Granulomatosis with polyangiitis (GPA, formerly Wegener's) classically hits sinuses, lungs and kidneys; microscopic polyangiitis (MPA) hits lungs and kidneys.",
          p:"<b>The one place in this list where a HIGH DLCO is the alarming result.</b> Blood inside the alveoli soaks up carbon monoxide, so alveolar haemorrhage <i>raises</i> the DLCO &mdash; a rising number here can mean bleeding, not improvement. GPA also causes subglottic stenosis (upper-airway narrowing), which shows as a flattened flow-volume loop. MPA more often produces fibrotic ILD &mdash; restriction, low DLCO.",
          watch:"You only catch the stenosis if the machine draws the loop &mdash; a number-only report hides it." },

        dyspnea: { c:'Presenting symptom', t:'Shortness of breath / dyspnea',
          w:"Breathlessness &mdash; the sensation of not getting enough air. Patients rarely use the word. They say they're \"winded,\" \"out of shape,\" or that the stairs have gotten harder.",
          p:"The most common presenting symptom of ILD, and the least specific &mdash; heart failure, anemia, deconditioning and lung disease all produce it. Spirometry is a recommended <b>first-line</b> test in the chronic-dyspnea workup precisely because it is cheap and settles the pulmonary half quickly.",
          watch:"In a rheumatology patient, documented dyspnea is what converts a screening question into defensible medical necessity (R06.00)." },

        cough: { c:'Presenting symptom', t:'Chronic or unexplained cough',
          w:"A cough lasting more than eight weeks with no obvious cause &mdash; not a cold, not reflux, not post-nasal drip, not an ACE inhibitor.",
          p:"ILD cough is characteristically <b>dry and non-productive</b>, and it often precedes breathlessness by months. It gets attributed to allergies or reflux for a long time before anybody measures the lungs &mdash; in a Sj&ouml;gren's patient it's blamed on dryness, in an RA patient on the drugs.",
          watch:"The cough can arrive while spirometry still reads normal. DLCO is usually the number that has already moved." },

        exertion: { c:'Presenting symptom', t:'Reduced exercise tolerance',
          w:"The patient is simply doing less than they used to &mdash; one flight of stairs instead of two, stopping to rest on a walk they used to finish. Usually described as age or weight rather than as a symptom.",
          p:"This is dyspnea the patient has <i>adapted to</i> instead of reported, and it is the most commonly missed ILD signal. People unconsciously reduce activity to stay under the threshold where they feel breathless &mdash; so they never complain of breathlessness at all.",
          watch:"Asking \"what could you do a year ago that's harder now?\" finds disease that \"any shortness of breath?\" misses entirely." },

        desat: { c:'Objective finding', t:'Unexplained oxygen desaturation',
          w:"The pulse-ox reading drops &mdash; either at rest or, far more often, only when the patient walks. In early ILD, resting saturation is typically normal and falls only under load.",
          p:"A meaningful red flag: it means the gas-exchange surface is already compromised enough to fail under demand. It tracks with the DLCO &mdash; the same failure of oxygen transfer across a scarred alveolar membrane, measured two different ways.",
          watch:"A normal resting pulse-ox does not rule out ILD. That gap is precisely what a measured DLCO fills." },

        crackles: { c:'Exam finding', t:'Bibasilar crackles on exam',
          w:"Fine crackling sounds at the bases of both lungs, heard through a stethoscope at the end of a breath in. Widely described as the sound of Velcro being pulled apart.",
          p:"<b>The most specific physical finding for ILD on this page &mdash; and it costs nothing.</b> \"Velcro crackles\" can be present before the patient has symptoms and before a chest X-ray shows anything. Fibrotic ILD is typically basal and peripheral, which is why the bases are where you hear it first.",
          watch:"Crackles plus a rheumatologic diagnosis is a strong, well-documented indication for the full panel." },

        newsx: { c:'Presenting symptom', t:'New respiratory symptoms on an immunosuppressant',
          w:"Any new breathlessness, cough, or drop in exercise tolerance that appears after starting or escalating an immunosuppressive drug.",
          p:"Deliberately the broadest trigger on this page, because <b>three different things produce it and they are treated in opposite directions</b>: (1) the underlying disease progressing to ILD, (2) drug-induced pneumonitis &mdash; the drug injuring the lung, (3) opportunistic infection, because the patient is immunosuppressed.",
          watch:"A PFT does not tell you which one. It establishes objectively that something changed, and gives a number to compare against baseline &mdash; which is the whole argument for having a baseline." },

        mtx: { c:'DMARD', t:'Methotrexate (MTX)',
          w:"The anchor drug of rheumatoid arthritis treatment &mdash; a low-dose weekly antimetabolite. Cheap, effective, and taken by a very large share of RA patients.",
          p:"The most famous lung reputation in rheumatology, and the most misunderstood. Methotrexate pneumonitis is real but <b>rare and idiosyncratic</b> &mdash; it can appear at any point, unrelated to dose or duration, so scheduled PFTs cannot predict it. A baseline is defensible. Routine surveillance of the asymptomatic patient is <b>not</b> evidence-supported, and the 2021 ACR RA guideline makes no such recommendation.",
          watch:"Sell the baseline and the symptomatic retest &mdash; never a standing test-everyone protocol. Monitoring code Z79.631." },

        cyc: { c:'Cytotoxic agent', t:'Cyclophosphamide (CYC)',
          w:"A potent alkylating chemotherapy agent, used in rheumatology for severe organ-threatening disease &mdash; scleroderma ILD, severe myositis, vasculitis with lung or kidney involvement.",
          p:"Prescribed <i>because</i> serious lung disease already exists, so these are the highest-frequency testing patients on the page &mdash; up to 4x a year. Here the PFT is the <b>efficacy readout, not a safety screen</b>: the FVC and DLCO trend is how you judge whether the drug is holding the line. Cyclophosphamide can itself cause fibrosis, including a late-onset form appearing years later.",
          watch:"Strongest medical-necessity story in Section 3 &mdash; documented disease, documented drug, documented reason to re-measure. Code Z79.630." },

        mmf: { c:'Immunosuppressant', t:'Mycophenolate mofetil (MMF / CellCept)',
          w:"An antimetabolite immunosuppressant. In scleroderma ILD it has largely displaced cyclophosphamide as first-line therapy &mdash; comparable lung benefit with a considerably better tolerability profile.",
          p:"Same logic as cyclophosphamide: prescribed because ILD exists, so the PFT is tracking whether the disease is stabilising. <b>FVC trend was the primary endpoint in the scleroderma trials</b>, which is why serial spirometry plus DLCO is the standard follow-up rather than an optional extra.",
          watch:"Shares monitoring code Z79.624 with azathioprine." },

        leflunomide: { c:'DMARD', t:'Leflunomide',
          w:"An oral DMARD for rheumatoid arthritis, generally used when methotrexate isn't tolerated or isn't enough on its own. Notably long half-life &mdash; it lingers in the body for weeks.",
          p:"Carries a pneumonitis risk similar in character to methotrexate's, with an extra wrinkle: because the half-life is so long, <b>stopping the drug does not clear it quickly</b>. Baseline PFT before starting, and a low threshold to retest the moment the patient reports anything respiratory.",
          watch:"Coding trap &mdash; leflunomide has NO drug-specific Z79.6&ndash; code. It genuinely stays Z79.899." },

        jak: { c:'Targeted synthetic DMARD', t:'JAK inhibitors',
          w:"Targeted oral drugs that block the Janus kinase signalling pathway &mdash; tofacitinib, baricitinib, upadacitinib. A newer class used in RA and other inflammatory disease.",
          p:"The lung concern here is less direct drug injury and more <b>infection risk</b> &mdash; this class carries a well-documented signal for serious and opportunistic infection, including tuberculosis reactivation and herpes zoster. So new respiratory symptoms on a JAK inhibitor should raise infection first, drug toxicity second.",
          watch:"PFTs quantify the functional change; imaging and workup answer the cause. Monitoring code Z79.622." },

        biologic: { c:'Biologic', t:'Immunosuppressive biologics',
          w:"Injected or infused antibody drugs that target one specific immune molecule &mdash; TNF inhibitors (adalimumab, etanercept, infliximab), rituximab (anti-CD20), tocilizumab (anti-IL-6), abatacept.",
          p:"Two distinct issues. <b>Infection risk</b>, particularly TB reactivation with TNF inhibitors &mdash; which is why TB screening precedes them. And a genuinely unsettled question about whether TNF inhibitors help or worsen RA-ILD, with case reports pointing both directions. Rituximab and abatacept are more often chosen when ILD is already present.",
          watch:"Objective serial lung function is what turns that judgement from anecdotal into measurable. Monitoring code Z79.620." },

        aza: { c:'Immunosuppressant', t:'Azathioprine',
          w:"An older antimetabolite immunosuppressant, used as a steroid-sparing agent across lupus, vasculitis and myositis, and sometimes as maintenance therapy after ILD induction treatment.",
          p:"Pulmonary toxicity is <b>uncommon</b> compared with methotrexate or cyclophosphamide, so the reason to test is usually the underlying disease rather than the drug itself. Where azathioprine is maintenance after induction, serial PFTs are how you confirm the remission is holding.",
          watch:"Shares monitoring code Z79.624 with MMF." },

        /* ---- Composer: the numbers and concepts on the report ---- */
        zscore: { c:'How results are scored', t:'Z-score',
          w:"How far this patient's result sits from the average for a healthy person of the <b>same age, height, sex and ethnicity</b> &mdash; counted in standard deviations. 0 is dead average. Negative is below average. &minus;1.645 is the cutoff.",
          p:"This is what replaced the old \"80% of predicted\" rule of thumb, and the reason matters: 80% predicted means very different things for a 25-year-old man and an 80-year-old woman. <b>The z-score has already done that adjustment</b>, so one threshold works for everybody. ATS/ERS 2022 recommends z-scores over fixed percentages.",
          watch:"&minus;1.645 is the 5th percentile &mdash; only 5% of genuinely healthy people fall below it. That's the whole idea behind LLN." },

        lln: { c:'The threshold', t:'LLN &mdash; lower limit of normal',
          w:"The statistical floor of the normal range: the 5th percentile of healthy people. It is the same thing as a z-score of &minus;1.645, just said differently.",
          p:"<b>The single line every gate in this tree is asking about.</b> Using LLN instead of a flat 80%-predicted cutoff avoids two classic errors in opposite directions &mdash; over-calling restriction in tall young patients, and missing real disease in older, shorter ones.",
          watch:"By definition 5% of perfectly healthy people fall below LLN. One borderline number is not a diagnosis &mdash; which is why the draft always goes to a physician." },

        pctpred: { c:'How results are scored', t:'% Predicted',
          w:"The result expressed as a percentage of what an average healthy person of the same age, height and sex would produce. 100% means exactly average.",
          p:"The familiar number, and still what most reports lead with &mdash; but <b>it does not account for the natural spread of normal</b>, which is why it's the fallback here rather than the first choice. Enter the z-score if the report gives you one.",
          watch:"It still has a job: %predicted is what ATS/ERS uses to <i>grade severity</i> once a pattern is identified. Both numbers earn their place." },

        ratio: { c:'Gate 1 &middot; Airflow', t:'FEV&#8321;/FVC ratio',
          w:"What fraction of their air the patient can blow out in the <b>first second</b>. If they can exhale 4 litres in total and 3 of it comes out in the first second, the ratio is 75%.",
          p:"<b>Gate 1 &mdash; the airflow question, and it always goes first.</b> Below LLN means <b>obstruction</b>: air is coming out too slowly because the airways are narrowed. Normal or high rules obstruction out and sends you to Gate 2.",
          watch:"Entering it as a raw decimal (0.78) instead of a percentage (78) is the most common entry error on this screen &mdash; the tool refuses to classify and warns you instead of silently misreading it." },

        tlc: { c:'Gate 2 &middot; Size', t:'TLC &mdash; total lung capacity',
          w:"The total volume of air the lungs hold when completely full. Plainly: the size of the container.",
          p:"<b>Gate 2 &mdash; and the only number that can truly confirm restriction.</b> Below LLN means the lungs are small. Spirometry alone cannot answer this: a low FVC only <i>suggests</i> small lungs, because FVC also falls in obstruction when trapped air stops the lungs emptying.",
          watch:"This is the argument for lung volumes (94726) rather than spirometry alone &mdash; without TLC you are guessing at restriction, not measuring it." },

        dlco: { c:'Gate 3 &middot; Gas exchange', t:'DLCO &mdash; diffusing capacity',
          w:"How well gas crosses from the air sacs into the bloodstream. Measured with a trace of carbon monoxide, which grabs onto hemoglobin far more readily than oxygen does. \"Corrected\" means adjusted for the patient's hemoglobin, since anemia lowers the result on its own.",
          p:"<b>Gate 3 &mdash; and in a rheumatology clinic, usually the most important number on the page.</b> It is frequently the <b>first thing to fall in ILD</b>, before the volumes move and before the patient feels anything. Restriction + low DLCO points at interstitial disease. Normal volumes + isolated low DLCO points at pulmonary vascular disease. A <i>high</i> DLCO can mean alveolar haemorrhage.",
          watch:"Billed as 94729, and it is an add-on &mdash; it must accompany 94010 or 94726/94727, never stand alone." },

        fvc: { c:'Supporting number', t:'FVC &mdash; forced vital capacity',
          w:"The total amount of air blown out in one hard, complete breath, starting from completely full lungs.",
          p:"The workhorse follow-up number. <b>The FVC trend &mdash; not any single reading &mdash; is the accepted measure of whether ILD is progressing or a drug is working</b>; it was the primary endpoint in the scleroderma treatment trials, which is why serial testing is the standard of care rather than an upsell.",
          watch:"A low FVC on its own does NOT prove restriction &mdash; it drops in obstruction too. TLC is what confirms it." },

        fev1: { c:'Supporting number', t:'FEV&#8321;',
          w:"The volume of air blown out in the first second of that hard, complete breath.",
          p:"It does two separate jobs. Paired with FVC it forms the <b>ratio</b> that answers Gate 1. On its own, as %predicted, it is what <b>grades severity</b> once a pattern is established.",
          watch:"It does not identify the pattern &mdash; the ratio, TLC and DLCO do that. FEV&#8321; only tells you how far along it is." },

        bmi: { c:'Confounder check', t:'BMI &mdash; body mass index',
          w:"Weight relative to height. Optional here, but it turns on an important check.",
          p:"<b>Obesity restricts lung volumes mechanically, with no lung disease present at all.</b> Weight on the chest wall and abdomen splints the diaphragm and lowers both FVC and TLC. The giveaway is reduced volumes with a <b>preserved or high DLCO</b> &mdash; the gas exchange surface is fine, the bellows is simply loaded.",
          watch:"Miss this and you label a heavy patient with ILD they don't have. The tool deliberately raises the question rather than answering it &mdash; that call belongs to the physician." },

        obstruction: { c:'Pattern', t:'Obstruction',
          w:"Air comes out too slowly, because the airways are narrowed, inflamed or floppy &mdash; asthma, COPD, bronchiolitis, bronchiectasis.",
          p:"Defined by a <b>FEV&#8321;/FVC ratio below LLN</b>. Not the pattern you are hunting in ILD screening &mdash; but it is exactly what turns up in <b>RA-related bronchiolitis obliterans</b> and in <b>Sj&ouml;gren's small-airway disease</b>.",
          watch:"That's precisely why the tree checks airflow before it checks size. Skip Gate 1 and you misread those two." },

        restriction: { c:'Pattern', t:'Restriction',
          w:"The lungs are small &mdash; they simply don't hold what they should. Either the lung tissue itself is stiff and scarred, or something outside it limits expansion: chest wall, obesity, weak muscles, pleural disease.",
          p:"Confirmed by a <b>TLC below LLN</b> alongside a normal-or-high ratio. <b>This is the pattern the whole estimator is built to catch</b>, because it is the signature of interstitial lung disease.",
          watch:"Restriction alone doesn't say <i>why</i>. Pair it with DLCO: low DLCO points at scarring in the tissue; preserved DLCO points at a bellows problem like obesity or muscle weakness." },

        gasexchange: { c:'What the lung is for', t:'Gas exchange',
          w:"The actual job of the lung &mdash; moving oxygen into the blood and carbon dioxide out, across the very thin membrane between air sac and capillary.",
          p:"This is what DLCO measures, and what volumes and flows simply cannot tell you. <b>A patient can move normal amounts of air at normal speeds and still be failing to transfer oxygen</b> &mdash; that is early ILD, and that is pulmonary vascular disease.",
          watch:"The strongest clinical argument for the full panel over spirometry alone, in one sentence: spirometry measures the bellows, DLCO measures the point of the whole exercise." },

        severity: { c:'Grading', t:'Severity grading',
          w:"Once a pattern has been identified, how far along it is &mdash; mild through very severe.",
          p:"Graded on <b>FEV&#8321; %predicted</b> under the ATS/ERS 2005 scheme. Note that this is a <i>separate step</i> from identifying the pattern, and that it is graded on the percentage rather than the z-score.",
          watch:"The MiniBox+ device and the ATS-2005 table can land one grade apart on the same case &mdash; which is exactly why this is an editable dropdown here and not a locked output." },

        hcq: { c:'Antimalarial', t:'Hydroxychloroquine',
          w:"An antimalarial used broadly in lupus, RA and Sj&ouml;gren's. The best-tolerated drug in the rheumatology cabinet &mdash; its well-known toxicity is retinal, not pulmonary.",
          p:"<b>Essentially no pulmonary toxicity signal. This drug on its own is not a reason to order a PFT.</b> It appears here because these patients very often carry a diagnosis that <i>is</i> a reason &mdash; lupus, RA, Sj&ouml;gren's.",
          watch:"Also a coding trap: no drug-specific Z79.6&ndash; code exists, so it stays Z79.899. If you test a hydroxychloroquine patient, the necessity must come from the disease or the symptom &mdash; never from the drug." }
      };

      var pop, hideT, showT, pinned = false, cur = null;

      function el(id){ return document.getElementById(id); }

      function build(k){
        var g = G[k]; if (!g) return false;
        el('rhl-cat').innerHTML = g.c;
        el('rhl-term').innerHTML = g.t;
        var h = '<div class="rhl-lbl">&#9679; What it is</div><p class="rhl-txt">' + g.w + '</p>' +
                '<div class="rhl-lbl pulm">&#9679; How it reads on a PFT</div>' +
                '<div class="rhl-pulm-box"><p class="rhl-txt">' + g.p + '</p></div>';
        if (g.watch) h += '<div class="rhl-watch"><span>&#9758;</span><div>' + g.watch + '</div></div>';
        el('rhl-body').innerHTML = h;
        return true;
      }

      function place(t){
        var body = el('rhl-body');
        body.style.maxHeight = '';
        pop.style.bottom = ''; pop.style.right = '';
        pop.style.left = '-9999px'; pop.style.top = '0px';
        pop.classList.add('rhl-show');

        // Phone: bottom sheet. Nudge the page so the term stays visible above it.
        if (window.innerWidth <= 640) {
          pop.style.left = ''; pop.style.top = '';
          requestAnimationFrame(function(){
            var pr = pop.getBoundingClientRect(), er = t.getBoundingClientRect();
            if (er.bottom > pr.top - 8) {
              window.scrollBy(0, Math.ceil(er.bottom - pr.top + 20));
            }
          });
          return;
        }

        // Desktop/tablet: open on whichever side has more room, and cap the card's
        // height to that space so it can never sit on top of the term itself.
        var gap = 9, edge = 10;
        var r = t.getBoundingClientRect();
        var below = window.innerHeight - r.bottom - gap - edge;
        var above = r.top - gap - edge;
        var useAbove = above > below;
        var avail = Math.max(above, below);

        var chrome = pop.offsetHeight - body.offsetHeight;   // header + footer
        if (pop.offsetHeight > avail) {
          body.style.maxHeight = Math.max(130, avail - chrome - 4) + 'px';
        }

        var pw = pop.offsetWidth, ph = pop.offsetHeight;
        var left = r.left + (r.width / 2) - (pw / 2);
        left = Math.max(edge, Math.min(left, window.innerWidth - pw - edge));
        var top = useAbove ? (r.top - gap - ph) : (r.bottom + gap);
        top = Math.max(edge, Math.min(top, window.innerHeight - ph - edge));

        pop.style.left = Math.round(left) + 'px';
        pop.style.top = Math.round(top) + 'px';
      }

      function open(t, pin){
        var k = t.getAttribute('data-gloss');
        clearTimeout(hideT);
        if (cur && cur !== t) cur.classList.remove('rhl-on');
        if (!build(k)) return;
        cur = t; t.classList.add('rhl-on');
        pinned = !!pin;
        place(t);
      }

      window.rhlClose = function(force){
        if (pinned && !force) return;
        pinned = false;
        pop.classList.remove('rhl-show');
        if (cur) { cur.classList.remove('rhl-on'); cur = null; }
      };

      function init(){
        pop = el('rhl-pop'); if (!pop) return;
        var terms = document.querySelectorAll('#tab-rheum .rh-learn[data-gloss]');
        for (var i = 0; i < terms.length; i++) {
          (function(t){
            t.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
            t.setAttribute('role', 'button');
            t.addEventListener('mouseenter', function(){
              if (pinned) return;
              clearTimeout(showT);
              showT = setTimeout(function(){ open(t, false); }, 130);
            });
            t.addEventListener('mouseleave', function(){
              clearTimeout(showT);
              if (pinned) return;
              hideT = setTimeout(function(){ window.rhlClose(); }, 220);
            });
            t.addEventListener('click', function(e){
              e.stopPropagation(); e.preventDefault();
              clearTimeout(showT);
              if (pinned && cur === t) { window.rhlClose(true); return; }
              open(t, true);
            });
            t.addEventListener('keydown', function(e){
              if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') { e.preventDefault(); open(t, true); }
            });
          })(terms[i]);
        }
        pop.addEventListener('mouseenter', function(){ clearTimeout(hideT); });
        pop.addEventListener('mouseleave', function(){ if (!pinned) window.rhlClose(); });
        document.addEventListener('click', function(e){
          if (pop.classList.contains('rhl-show') && !pop.contains(e.target)) window.rhlClose(true);
        });
        document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e){
          if (e.key === 'Escape' && pop.classList.contains('rhl-show')) window.rhlClose(true);
        });
        window.addEventListener('resize', function(){ if (pop.classList.contains('rhl-show')) window.rhlClose(true); });
        window.addEventListener('scroll', function(){ if (pop.classList.contains('rhl-show') && !pinned) window.rhlClose(true); }, true);
      }

      if (document.readyState === 'loading') document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);
      else init();
    })();
    </script>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================ PULMONOLOGY ============================ -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-pulmo">
    <style>
      #tab-pulmo .plp { --plt:#185fa5; --plt-deep:#0f4a85; --plt-wash:#eff6ff; --plt-line:#d5e4f5; --plink:#0e2438; --plsoft:#3e556b; --plg:#c98a2b; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-lede { font-size:14.5px; color:var(--plsoft); max-width:680px; line-height:1.6; margin:2px 0 4px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-sec { margin-top:26px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-sec-head { display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:11px; margin-bottom:14px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-sec-num { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono','Consolas',monospace; font-size:13px; font-weight:600; color:var(--plg); }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-sec-title { font-size:18px; font-weight:800; color:var(--plink); letter-spacing:-.01em; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-steps { display:grid; gap:10px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-step { display:grid; grid-template-columns:auto 1fr; gap:16px; align-items:start; background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--plt-line); border-radius:12px; padding:15px 18px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-step .plp-n { font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; font-size:24px; font-weight:600; color:var(--plt); line-height:1; min-width:26px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-step h4 { font-size:14.5px; font-weight:700; color:var(--plink); margin:0 0 3px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-step p { font-size:13px; color:var(--plsoft); margin:0; line-height:1.55; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-stats { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:12px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-stat { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--plt-line); border-left:4px solid var(--plt); border-radius:11px; padding:16px 18px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-stat .plp-big { font-size:30px; font-weight:800; color:var(--plink); line-height:1; font-family:'DM Mono','SF Mono',monospace; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-stat .plp-lbl { margin-top:7px; font-size:12.5px; color:var(--plsoft); line-height:1.45; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-grid2 { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:14px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-ref { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--plt-line); border-radius:12px; padding:18px 20px; }
      #tab-pulmo .plp-ref h4 { font-size:11.5px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.11em; color:var(--plt-deep); font-weight:800; margin:0 0 12px; }
