    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#185fa5;color:#fff;">&#129729;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Pulmonology</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Your primary call point &mdash; the complete resource: the play, the proof, the calculators, and every file ready to email</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="plsub-nav">
      <button type="button" class="plsub-btn on" id="plsub-playbook" onclick="pulmoShowView('playbook', this)">&#128214; The Playbook</button>
      <button type="button" class="plsub-btn"    id="plsub-calcs"    onclick="pulmoShowView('calcs', this)">&#129518; Calculators</button>
      <button type="button" class="plsub-btn"    id="plsub-files"    onclick="pulmoShowView('files', this)">&#128193; Files &amp; Templates</button>
    </div>

    <div id="pulmo-view-playbook" class="plp">
      <div class="plp-files-cta">
        <div>
          <div class="plp-files-cta-h">&#128193; Everything for the pulmonology call &mdash; ready to email</div>
          <div class="plp-files-cta-s">The brochure, the CHEST 2021 validation, the sample report, the ROI &amp; billing calculators &mdash; every file and tool in one place.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="plp-files-cta-btns">
          <button type="button" onclick="pulmoShowView('files', document.getElementById('plsub-files'))">Open the files</button>
          <button type="button" class="ghost" onclick="pulmoEmailAll()">&#9993; Email the core pack</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="plp-lede">Pulmonologists already believe in full PFTs &mdash; the sell isn&rsquo;t the science, it&rsquo;s the <strong>capacity</strong>. The body box is room-sized, tech-dependent, and booked out for weeks. MiniBox+ puts spirometry, lung volumes, and DLCO in the exam room and in the satellite office.</div>

      <div class="plp-sec">
        <div class="plp-sec-head"><span class="plp-sec-num">01</span><span class="plp-sec-title">The play, in five moves</span></div>
        <div class="plp-steps">
          <div class="plp-step"><div class="plp-n">1</div><div><h4>Don&rsquo;t fight the body box &mdash; flank it</h4><p>Never position MiniBox+ as a body-box replacement. It&rsquo;s for satellite offices, overflow days, and same-visit workups &mdash; the box stays for complex cases while they recover weeks of scheduling capacity.</p></div></div>
          <div class="plp-step"><div class="plp-n">2</div><div><h4>Find the backlog</h4><p>Ask how far out the PFT lab is booked. Every week of backlog is a delayed diagnosis, a rescheduled patient, and revenue waiting in line. That backlog is your opening.</p></div></div>
          <div class="plp-step"><div class="plp-n">3</div><div><h4>Lead with the hero line</h4><p><strong>&ldquo;Full PFTs &mdash; spirometry, lung volumes, DLCO &mdash; in the exam room, in under 15 minutes, without a sealed booth.&rdquo;</strong></p></div></div>
          <div class="plp-step"><div class="plp-n">4</div><div><h4>Bring the validation, not the brochure</h4><p>This audience reads the literature. The CHEST 2021 Berger et al. study validated MiniBox+ TLC against plethysmography in 100+ subjects &mdash; hand the reprint across the desk (it&rsquo;s in the Email Library, ready to send).</p></div></div>
          <div class="plp-step"><div class="plp-n">5</div><div><h4>Close on capacity math</h4><p>Same-day workup means faster Rx decisions and no lost referrals to the schedule. Run the ROI calculator (Daily Hub) at their satellite-office volume and let the numbers close.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="plp-sec">
        <div class="plp-sec-head"><span class="plp-sec-num">02</span><span class="plp-sec-title">Why they listen</span></div>
        <div class="plp-stats">
          <div class="plp-stat"><div class="plp-big">&lt;15 min</div><div class="plp-lbl">complete PFT &mdash; spirometry, lung volumes, DLCO &mdash; in an exam room, no sealed booth</div></div>
          <div class="plp-stat"><div class="plp-big">CHEST&nbsp;&rsquo;21</div><div class="plp-lbl">Berger et al. validation &mdash; MiniBox+ TLC vs. plethysmography, 100+ subjects</div></div>
          <div class="plp-stat"><div class="plp-big">Same day</div><div class="plp-lbl">workup and treatment decision at the visit the patient already showed up for</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="plp-sec">
        <div class="plp-sec-head"><span class="plp-sec-num">03</span><span class="plp-sec-title">Four questions that open the call</span></div>
        <div class="plp-qs">
          <div class="plp-qitem"><p>How far out is your PFT lab booked right now?</p></div>
          <div class="plp-qitem"><p>How many of your satellite offices can run full PFTs today &mdash; and what happens to those patients?</p></div>
          <div class="plp-qitem"><p>When a patient can&rsquo;t make it back for the lab appointment, how does that change the workup?</p></div>
          <div class="plp-qitem plp-closer"><span class="plp-qtag">The closer</span><p>If you could run spirometry, lung volumes, and DLCO in the exam room in fifteen minutes &mdash; which office would you put it in first?</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="plp-sec">
        <div class="plp-sec-head"><span class="plp-sec-num">04</span><span class="plp-sec-title">Quick reference</span></div>
        <div class="plp-grid2">
          <div class="plp-ref">
            <h4>What a full PFT bills</h4>
            <div class="plp-cpt"><span class="plp-cpt-code">94010</span><span class="plp-cpt-desc">Spirometry</span></div>
            <div class="plp-cpt"><span class="plp-cpt-code">94060</span><span class="plp-cpt-desc">Spirometry, pre &amp; post bronchodilator</span></div>
            <div class="plp-cpt"><span class="plp-cpt-code">94375</span><span class="plp-cpt-desc">Flow volume loop</span></div>
            <div class="plp-cpt"><span class="plp-cpt-code">94726</span><span class="plp-cpt-desc">Lung volumes / plethysmography (TLC)</span></div>
            <div class="plp-cpt"><span class="plp-cpt-code">94729</span><span class="plp-cpt-desc">DLCO (diffusing capacity)</span></div>
            <div class="plp-note"><b>Current dollar rates</b> live in the CPT &amp; Revenue tab and the Billing Helper &mdash; they update from one master rate table, so quote from there.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="plp-ref">
            <h4>The three objections, answered</h4>
            <div class="plp-obj"><div class="plp-q">&ldquo;We already have a body box.&rdquo;</div><div class="plp-a">Perfect &mdash; keep it. MiniBox+ is for satellite offices and overflow days. You keep the box for complex cases and recover weeks of scheduling capacity.</div></div>
            <div class="plp-obj"><div class="plp-q">&ldquo;Is it as accurate as plethysmography?&rdquo;</div><div class="plp-a">CHEST 2021, Berger et al. &mdash; MiniBox+ TLC validated against plethysmography in 100+ subjects. Offer the reprint, not a claim.</div></div>
            <div class="plp-obj"><div class="plp-q">&ldquo;My techs are already stretched.&rdquo;</div><div class="plp-a">MiniBox+ was built for exam-room use &mdash; an MA runs it after a short training, and results land in the EMR in minutes. No booth, no dedicated tech.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="plp-sec">
        <div class="plp-sec-head"><span class="plp-sec-num">05</span><span class="plp-sec-title">The ask</span></div>
        <div class="plp-ref" style="border-left:4px solid var(--plg);">
          <div style="font-size:14px; font-weight:700; color:var(--plink); margin-bottom:4px;">Schedule a 30-minute in-office demo.</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px; color:var(--plsoft); line-height:1.55;">Bring the Berger reprint and run the numbers live &mdash; the ROI, financing, and PFT-coding tools are one tap away in <strong>&#129518; Calculators</strong> above, and every leave-behind is in <strong>&#128193; Files &amp; Templates</strong>, ready to email in one send.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div><!-- end pulmo-view-playbook -->

    <!-- ============ VIEW: CALCULATORS ============ -->
    <div id="pulmo-view-calcs" class="plp" style="display:none;">
      <div class="plp-lede">Three interactive tools for the pulmonology call &mdash; run them live in the exam room or send them ahead. <strong>Open</strong> launches the tool in a new tab, <strong>Download</strong> saves it, <strong>Email it</strong> sends it as a working file the practice opens in their own browser (works offline).</div>
      <div id="pulmo-calcs-grid" style="margin-top:16px;"><!-- rendered by toolkit v3 engine --></div>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ VIEW: FILES & TEMPLATES ============ -->
    <div id="pulmo-view-files" class="plp" style="display:none;">
      <div class="plp-lede">Every pulmonology leave-behind in one place &mdash; the brochure, the CHEST 2021 validation, the sample report, competitive comparison, and the IT/technical docs. <strong>View</strong> reads it, <strong>Download</strong> saves it, <strong>Email it</strong> jumps to the Email Center with the file genuinely attached &mdash; no manual attaching.</div>
      <div style="margin:14px 0;">
        <button class="eas-web-btn" style="background:#185fa5;" onclick="pulmoEmailAll()" title="Loads the core pulmonology leave-behind pack into the Email Center as attachments">&#9993; Email the core pulmonology pack</button>
      </div>
      <div id="pulmo-files-grid"><!-- rendered by toolkit v3 engine --></div>
    </div>
  </div>

